55static bool ignoreCallingConv(LibFunc Func) {
56 return Func == LibFunc_abs || Func == LibFunc_labs ||
57 Func == LibFunc_llabs || Func == LibFunc_strlen;
58}
59
60static bool isCallingConvCCompatible(CallInst *CI) {
61 switch(CI->getCallingConv()) {
62 default:
63 return false;
64 case llvm::CallingConv::C:
65 return true;
66 case llvm::CallingConv::ARM_APCS:
67 case llvm::CallingConv::ARM_AAPCS:
68 case llvm::CallingConv::ARM_AAPCS_VFP: {
69
70 // The iOS ABI diverges from the standard in some cases, so for now don't
71 // try to simplify those calls.
72 if (Triple(CI->getModule()->getTargetTriple()).isiOS())
73 return false;
74
75 auto *FuncTy = CI->getFunctionType();
76
77 if (!FuncTy->getReturnType()->isPointerTy() &&
78 !FuncTy->getReturnType()->isIntegerTy() &&
79 !FuncTy->getReturnType()->isVoidTy())
80 return false;
81
82 for (auto Param : FuncTy->params()) {
83 if (!Param->isPointerTy() && !Param->isIntegerTy())
84 return false;
85 }
86 return true;
87 }
88 }
89 return false;
90}
91
92/// Return true if it is only used in equality comparisons with With.
93static bool isOnlyUsedInEqualityComparison(Value *V, Value *With) {
94 for (User *U : V->users()) {
95 if (ICmpInst *IC = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(U))
96 if (IC->isEquality() && IC->getOperand(1) == With)
97 continue;
98 // Unknown instruction.
99 return false;
100 }
101 return true;
102}

104static bool callHasFloatingPointArgument(const CallInst *CI) {
105 return any_of(CI->operands(), [](const Use &OI) {
106 return OI->getType()->isFloatingPointTy();
107 });
108}
109
110static bool callHasFP128Argument(const CallInst *CI) {
111 return any_of(CI->operands(), [](const Use &OI) {
112 return OI->getType()->isFP128Ty();
113 });
114}

116static Value *convertStrToNumber(CallInst *CI, StringRef &Str, int64_t Base) {
117 if (Base < 2 || Base > 36)
118 // handle special zero base
119 if (Base != 0)
120 return nullptr;
121
122 char *End;
123 std::string nptr = Str.str();
124 errno = 0;
125 long long int Result = strtoll(nptr.c_str(), &End, Base);
126 if (errno)
127 return nullptr;
128
129 // if we assume all possible target locales are ASCII supersets,
130 // then if strtoll successfully parses a number on the host,
131 // it will also successfully parse the same way on the target
132 if (*End != '\0')
133 return nullptr;
134
135 if (!isIntN(CI->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits(), Result))
136 return nullptr;
137
138 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Result);
139}
140
141static bool isLocallyOpenedFile(Value *File, CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B,
142 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) {
143 CallInst *FOpen = dyn_cast<CallInst>(File);
144 if (!FOpen)
145 return false;
146
147 Function *InnerCallee = FOpen->getCalledFunction();
148 if (!InnerCallee)
149 return false;
150
151 LibFunc Func;
152 if (!TLI->getLibFunc(*InnerCallee, Func) || !TLI->has(Func) ||
153 Func != LibFunc_fopen)
154 return false;
155
156 inferLibFuncAttributes(*CI->getCalledFunction(), *TLI);
157 if (PointerMayBeCaptured(File, true, true))
158 return false;
159
160 return true;
161}
162
163static bool isOnlyUsedInComparisonWithZero(Value *V) {
164 for (User *U : V->users()) {
165 if (ICmpInst *IC = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(U))
166 if (Constant *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(IC->getOperand(1)))
167 if (C->isNullValue())
168 continue;
169 // Unknown instruction.
170 return false;
171 }
172 return true;
173}
174
175static bool canTransformToMemCmp(CallInst *CI, Value *Str, uint64_t Len,
176 const DataLayout &DL) {
177 if (!isOnlyUsedInComparisonWithZero(CI))
178 return false;
179
180 if (!isDereferenceableAndAlignedPointer(Str, 1, APInt(64, Len), DL))
181 return false;
182
183 if (CI->getFunction()->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::SanitizeMemory))
184 return false;
185
186 return true;
187}

193Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrCat(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
194 // Extract some information from the instruction
195 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0);
196 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1);
197
198 // See if we can get the length of the input string.
199 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(Src);
200 if (Len == 0)
201 return nullptr;
202 --Len; // Unbias length.
203
204 // Handle the simple, do-nothing case: strcat(x, "") -> x
205 if (Len == 0)
206 return Dst;
207
208 return emitStrLenMemCpy(Src, Dst, Len, B);
209}
210
211Value *LibCallSimplifier::emitStrLenMemCpy(Value *Src, Value *Dst, uint64_t Len,
212 IRBuilder<> &B) {
213 // We need to find the end of the destination string. That's where the
214 // memory is to be moved to. We just generate a call to strlen.
215 Value *DstLen = emitStrLen(Dst, B, DL, TLI);
216 if (!DstLen)
217 return nullptr;
218
219 // Now that we have the destination's length, we must index into the
220 // destination's pointer to get the actual memcpy destination (end of
221 // the string .. we're concatenating).
222 Value *CpyDst = B.CreateGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, DstLen, "endptr");
223
224 // We have enough information to now generate the memcpy call to do the
225 // concatenation for us. Make a memcpy to copy the nul byte with align = 1.
226 B.CreateMemCpy(CpyDst, 1, Src, 1,
227 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(Src->getContext()), Len + 1));
228 return Dst;
229}
230
231Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrNCat(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
232 // Extract some information from the instruction.
233 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0);
234 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1);
235 uint64_t Len;
236
237 // We don't do anything if length is not constant.
238 if (ConstantInt *LengthArg = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(2)))
239 Len = LengthArg->getZExtValue();
240 else
241 return nullptr;
242
243 // See if we can get the length of the input string.
244 uint64_t SrcLen = GetStringLength(Src);
245 if (SrcLen == 0)
246 return nullptr;
247 --SrcLen; // Unbias length.
248
249 // Handle the simple, do-nothing cases:
250 // strncat(x, "", c) -> x
251 // strncat(x, c, 0) -> x
252 if (SrcLen == 0 || Len == 0)
253 return Dst;
254
255 // We don't optimize this case.
256 if (Len < SrcLen)
257 return nullptr;
258
259 // strncat(x, s, c) -> strcat(x, s)
260 // s is constant so the strcat can be optimized further.
261 return emitStrLenMemCpy(Src, Dst, SrcLen, B);
262}
263
264Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrChr(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
265 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
266 FunctionType *FT = Callee->getFunctionType();
267 Value *SrcStr = CI->getArgOperand(0);
268
269 // If the second operand is non-constant, see if we can compute the length
270 // of the input string and turn this into memchr.
271 ConstantInt *CharC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(1));
272 if (!CharC) {
273 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(SrcStr);
274 if (Len == 0 || !FT->getParamType(1)->isIntegerTy(32)) // memchr needs i32.
275 return nullptr;
276
277 return emitMemChr(SrcStr, CI->getArgOperand(1), // include nul.
278 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len),
279 B, DL, TLI);
280 }
281
282 // Otherwise, the character is a constant, see if the first argument is
283 // a string literal. If so, we can constant fold.
284 StringRef Str;
285 if (!getConstantStringInfo(SrcStr, Str)) {
286 if (CharC->isZero()) // strchr(p, 0) -> p + strlen(p)
287 return B.CreateGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, emitStrLen(SrcStr, B, DL, TLI),
288 "strchr");
289 return nullptr;
290 }
291
292 // Compute the offset, make sure to handle the case when we're searching for
293 // zero (a weird way to spell strlen).
294 size_t I = (0xFF & CharC->getSExtValue()) == 0
295 ? Str.size()
296 : Str.find(CharC->getSExtValue());
297 if (I == StringRef::npos) // Didn't find the char. strchr returns null.
298 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
299
300 // strchr(s+n,c) -> gep(s+n+i,c)
301 return B.CreateGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, B.getInt64(I), "strchr");
302}
303
304Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrRChr(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
305 Value *SrcStr = CI->getArgOperand(0);
306 ConstantInt *CharC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(1));
307
308 // Cannot fold anything if we're not looking for a constant.
309 if (!CharC)
310 return nullptr;
311
312 StringRef Str;
313 if (!getConstantStringInfo(SrcStr, Str)) {
314 // strrchr(s, 0) -> strchr(s, 0)
315 if (CharC->isZero())
316 return emitStrChr(SrcStr, '\0', B, TLI);
317 return nullptr;
318 }
319
320 // Compute the offset.
321 size_t I = (0xFF & CharC->getSExtValue()) == 0
322 ? Str.size()
323 : Str.rfind(CharC->getSExtValue());
324 if (I == StringRef::npos) // Didn't find the char. Return null.
325 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
326
327 // strrchr(s+n,c) -> gep(s+n+i,c)
328 return B.CreateGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, B.getInt64(I), "strrchr");
329}
330
331Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrCmp(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
332 Value *Str1P = CI->getArgOperand(0), *Str2P = CI->getArgOperand(1);
333 if (Str1P == Str2P) // strcmp(x,x) -> 0
334 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0);
335
336 StringRef Str1, Str2;
337 bool HasStr1 = getConstantStringInfo(Str1P, Str1);
338 bool HasStr2 = getConstantStringInfo(Str2P, Str2);
339
340 // strcmp(x, y) -> cnst (if both x and y are constant strings)
341 if (HasStr1 && HasStr2)
342 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Str1.compare(Str2));
343
344 if (HasStr1 && Str1.empty()) // strcmp("", x) -> -*x
345 return B.CreateNeg(B.CreateZExt(
346 B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), Str2P, "strcmpload"), CI->getType()));
347
348 if (HasStr2 && Str2.empty()) // strcmp(x,"") -> *x
349 return B.CreateZExt(B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), Str1P, "strcmpload"),
350 CI->getType());
351
352 // strcmp(P, "x") -> memcmp(P, "x", 2)
353 uint64_t Len1 = GetStringLength(Str1P);
354 uint64_t Len2 = GetStringLength(Str2P);
355 if (Len1 && Len2) {
356 return emitMemCmp(Str1P, Str2P,
357 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()),
358 std::min(Len1, Len2)),
359 B, DL, TLI);
360 }
361
362 // strcmp to memcmp
363 if (!HasStr1 && HasStr2) {
364 if (canTransformToMemCmp(CI, Str1P, Len2, DL))
365 return emitMemCmp(
366 Str1P, Str2P,
367 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len2), B, DL,
368 TLI);
369 } else if (HasStr1 && !HasStr2) {
370 if (canTransformToMemCmp(CI, Str2P, Len1, DL))
371 return emitMemCmp(
372 Str1P, Str2P,
373 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len1), B, DL,
374 TLI);
375 }
376
377 return nullptr;
378}

380Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrNCmp(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
381 Value *Str1P = CI->getArgOperand(0), *Str2P = CI->getArgOperand(1);
382 if (Str1P == Str2P) // strncmp(x,x,n) -> 0
383 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0);
384
385 // Get the length argument if it is constant.
386 uint64_t Length;
387 if (ConstantInt *LengthArg = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(2)))
388 Length = LengthArg->getZExtValue();
389 else
390 return nullptr;
391
392 if (Length == 0) // strncmp(x,y,0) -> 0
393 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0);
394
395 if (Length == 1) // strncmp(x,y,1) -> memcmp(x,y,1)
396 return emitMemCmp(Str1P, Str2P, CI->getArgOperand(2), B, DL, TLI);
397
398 StringRef Str1, Str2;
399 bool HasStr1 = getConstantStringInfo(Str1P, Str1);
400 bool HasStr2 = getConstantStringInfo(Str2P, Str2);
401
402 // strncmp(x, y) -> cnst (if both x and y are constant strings)
403 if (HasStr1 && HasStr2) {
404 StringRef SubStr1 = Str1.substr(0, Length);
405 StringRef SubStr2 = Str2.substr(0, Length);
406 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), SubStr1.compare(SubStr2));
407 }
408
409 if (HasStr1 && Str1.empty()) // strncmp("", x, n) -> -*x
410 return B.CreateNeg(B.CreateZExt(
411 B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), Str2P, "strcmpload"), CI->getType()));
412
413 if (HasStr2 && Str2.empty()) // strncmp(x, "", n) -> *x
414 return B.CreateZExt(B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), Str1P, "strcmpload"),
415 CI->getType());
416
417 uint64_t Len1 = GetStringLength(Str1P);
418 uint64_t Len2 = GetStringLength(Str2P);
419
420 // strncmp to memcmp
421 if (!HasStr1 && HasStr2) {
422 Len2 = std::min(Len2, Length);
423 if (canTransformToMemCmp(CI, Str1P, Len2, DL))
424 return emitMemCmp(
425 Str1P, Str2P,
426 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len2), B, DL,
427 TLI);
428 } else if (HasStr1 && !HasStr2) {
429 Len1 = std::min(Len1, Length);
430 if (canTransformToMemCmp(CI, Str2P, Len1, DL))
431 return emitMemCmp(
432 Str1P, Str2P,
433 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len1), B, DL,
434 TLI);
435 }
436
437 return nullptr;
438}

440Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrCpy(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
441 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0), *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1);
442 if (Dst == Src) // strcpy(x,x) -> x
443 return Src;
444
445 // See if we can get the length of the input string.
446 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(Src);
447 if (Len == 0)
448 return nullptr;
449
450 // We have enough information to now generate the memcpy call to do the
451 // copy for us. Make a memcpy to copy the nul byte with align = 1.
452 B.CreateMemCpy(Dst, 1, Src, 1,
453 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len));
454 return Dst;
455}
456
457Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStpCpy(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
458 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
459 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0), *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1);
460 if (Dst == Src) { // stpcpy(x,x) -> x+strlen(x)
461 Value *StrLen = emitStrLen(Src, B, DL, TLI);
462 return StrLen ? B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, StrLen) : nullptr;
463 }
464
465 // See if we can get the length of the input string.
466 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(Src);
467 if (Len == 0)
468 return nullptr;
469
470 Type *PT = Callee->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0);
471 Value *LenV = ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(PT), Len);
472 Value *DstEnd = B.CreateGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst,
473 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(PT), Len - 1));
474
475 // We have enough information to now generate the memcpy call to do the
476 // copy for us. Make a memcpy to copy the nul byte with align = 1.
477 B.CreateMemCpy(Dst, 1, Src, 1, LenV);
478 return DstEnd;
479}

481Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrNCpy(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
482 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
483 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0);
484 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1);
485 Value *LenOp = CI->getArgOperand(2);
486
487 // See if we can get the length of the input string.
488 uint64_t SrcLen = GetStringLength(Src);
489 if (SrcLen == 0)
490 return nullptr;
491 --SrcLen;
492
493 if (SrcLen == 0) {
494 // strncpy(x, "", y) -> memset(align 1 x, '\0', y)
495 B.CreateMemSet(Dst, B.getInt8('\0'), LenOp, 1);
496 return Dst;
497 }
498
499 uint64_t Len;
500 if (ConstantInt *LengthArg = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(LenOp))
501 Len = LengthArg->getZExtValue();
502 else
503 return nullptr;
504
505 if (Len == 0)
506 return Dst; // strncpy(x, y, 0) -> x
507
508 // Let strncpy handle the zero padding
509 if (Len > SrcLen + 1)
510 return nullptr;
511
512 Type *PT = Callee->getFunctionType()->getParamType(0);
513 // strncpy(x, s, c) -> memcpy(align 1 x, align 1 s, c) [s and c are constant]
514 B.CreateMemCpy(Dst, 1, Src, 1, ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(PT), Len));
515
516 return Dst;
517}
518
519Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStringLength(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B,
520 unsigned CharSize) {
521 Value *Src = CI->getArgOperand(0);
522
523 // Constant folding: strlen("xyz") -> 3
524 if (uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(Src, CharSize))
525 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Len - 1);
526
527 // If s is a constant pointer pointing to a string literal, we can fold
528 // strlen(s + x) to strlen(s) - x, when x is known to be in the range
529 // [0, strlen(s)] or the string has a single null terminator '\0' at the end.
530 // We only try to simplify strlen when the pointer s points to an array
531 // of i8. Otherwise, we would need to scale the offset x before doing the
532 // subtraction. This will make the optimization more complex, and it's not
533 // very useful because calling strlen for a pointer of other types is
534 // very uncommon.
535 if (GEPOperator *GEP = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(Src)) {
536 if (!isGEPBasedOnPointerToString(GEP, CharSize))
537 return nullptr;
538
539 ConstantDataArraySlice Slice;
540 if (getConstantDataArrayInfo(GEP->getOperand(0), Slice, CharSize)) {
541 uint64_t NullTermIdx;
542 if (Slice.Array == nullptr) {
543 NullTermIdx = 0;
544 } else {
545 NullTermIdx = ~((uint64_t)0);
546 for (uint64_t I = 0, E = Slice.Length; I < E; ++I) {
547 if (Slice.Array->getElementAsInteger(I + Slice.Offset) == 0) {
548 NullTermIdx = I;
549 break;
550 }
551 }
552 // If the string does not have '\0', leave it to strlen to compute
553 // its length.
554 if (NullTermIdx == ~((uint64_t)0))
555 return nullptr;
556 }
557
558 Value *Offset = GEP->getOperand(2);
559 KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(Offset, DL, 0, nullptr, CI, nullptr);
560 Known.Zero.flipAllBits();
561 uint64_t ArrSize =
562 cast<ArrayType>(GEP->getSourceElementType())->getNumElements();
563
564 // KnownZero's bits are flipped, so zeros in KnownZero now represent
565 // bits known to be zeros in Offset, and ones in KnowZero represent
566 // bits unknown in Offset. Therefore, Offset is known to be in range
567 // [0, NullTermIdx] when the flipped KnownZero is non-negative and
568 // unsigned-less-than NullTermIdx.
569 //
570 // If Offset is not provably in the range [0, NullTermIdx], we can still
571 // optimize if we can prove that the program has undefined behavior when
572 // Offset is outside that range. That is the case when GEP->getOperand(0)
573 // is a pointer to an object whose memory extent is NullTermIdx+1.
574 if ((Known.Zero.isNonNegative() && Known.Zero.ule(NullTermIdx)) ||
575 (GEP->isInBounds() && isa<GlobalVariable>(GEP->getOperand(0)) &&
576 NullTermIdx == ArrSize - 1)) {
577 Offset = B.CreateSExtOrTrunc(Offset, CI->getType());
578 return B.CreateSub(ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), NullTermIdx),
579 Offset);
580 }
581 }
582
583 return nullptr;
584 }
585
586 // strlen(x?"foo":"bars") --> x ? 3 : 4
587 if (SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(Src)) {
588 uint64_t LenTrue = GetStringLength(SI->getTrueValue(), CharSize);
589 uint64_t LenFalse = GetStringLength(SI->getFalseValue(), CharSize);
590 if (LenTrue && LenFalse) {
591 ORE.emit([&]() {
592 return OptimizationRemark("instcombine", "simplify-libcalls", CI)
593 << "folded strlen(select) to select of constants";
594 });
595 return B.CreateSelect(SI->getCondition(),
596 ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), LenTrue - 1),
597 ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), LenFalse - 1));
598 }
599 }
600
601 // strlen(x) != 0 --> *x != 0
602 // strlen(x) == 0 --> *x == 0
603 if (isOnlyUsedInZeroEqualityComparison(CI))
604 return B.CreateZExt(B.CreateLoad(B.getIntNTy(CharSize), Src, "strlenfirst"),
605 CI->getType());
606
607 return nullptr;
608}
609
610Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrLen(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
611 return optimizeStringLength(CI, B, 8);
612}

614Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeWcslen(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
615 Module &M = *CI->getModule();
616 unsigned WCharSize = TLI->getWCharSize(M) * 8;
617 // We cannot perform this optimization without wchar_size metadata.
618 if (WCharSize == 0)
619 return nullptr;
620
621 return optimizeStringLength(CI, B, WCharSize);
622}

624Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrPBrk(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
625 StringRef S1, S2;
626 bool HasS1 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), S1);
627 bool HasS2 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), S2);
628
629 // strpbrk(s, "") -> nullptr
630 // strpbrk("", s) -> nullptr
631 if ((HasS1 && S1.empty()) || (HasS2 && S2.empty()))
632 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
633
634 // Constant folding.
635 if (HasS1 && HasS2) {
636 size_t I = S1.find_first_of(S2);
637 if (I == StringRef::npos) // No match.
638 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
639
640 return B.CreateGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), CI->getArgOperand(0), B.getInt64(I),
641 "strpbrk");
642 }
643
644 // strpbrk(s, "a") -> strchr(s, 'a')
645 if (HasS2 && S2.size() == 1)
646 return emitStrChr(CI->getArgOperand(0), S2[0], B, TLI);
647
648 return nullptr;
649}
650
651Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrTo(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
652 Value *EndPtr = CI->getArgOperand(1);
653 if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(EndPtr)) {
654 // With a null EndPtr, this function won't capture the main argument.
655 // It would be readonly too, except that it still may write to errno.
656 CI->addParamAttr(0, Attribute::NoCapture);
657 }
658
659 return nullptr;
660}

662Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrSpn(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
663 StringRef S1, S2;
664 bool HasS1 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), S1);
665 bool HasS2 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), S2);
666
667 // strspn(s, "") -> 0
668 // strspn("", s) -> 0
669 if ((HasS1 && S1.empty()) || (HasS2 && S2.empty()))
670 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
671
672 // Constant folding.
673 if (HasS1 && HasS2) {
674 size_t Pos = S1.find_first_not_of(S2);
675 if (Pos == StringRef::npos)
676 Pos = S1.size();
677 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Pos);
678 }
679
680 return nullptr;
681}

683Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrCSpn(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
684 StringRef S1, S2;
685 bool HasS1 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), S1);
686 bool HasS2 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), S2);
687
688 // strcspn("", s) -> 0
689 if (HasS1 && S1.empty())
690 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
691
692 // Constant folding.
693 if (HasS1 && HasS2) {
694 size_t Pos = S1.find_first_of(S2);
695 if (Pos == StringRef::npos)
696 Pos = S1.size();
697 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Pos);
698 }
699
700 // strcspn(s, "") -> strlen(s)
701 if (HasS2 && S2.empty())
702 return emitStrLen(CI->getArgOperand(0), B, DL, TLI);
703
704 return nullptr;
705}
706
707Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrStr(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
708 // fold strstr(x, x) -> x.
709 if (CI->getArgOperand(0) == CI->getArgOperand(1))
710 return B.CreateBitCast(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getType());
711
712 // fold strstr(a, b) == a -> strncmp(a, b, strlen(b)) == 0
713 if (isOnlyUsedInEqualityComparison(CI, CI->getArgOperand(0))) {
714 Value *StrLen = emitStrLen(CI->getArgOperand(1), B, DL, TLI);
715 if (!StrLen)
716 return nullptr;
717 Value *StrNCmp = emitStrNCmp(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1),
718 StrLen, B, DL, TLI);
719 if (!StrNCmp)
720 return nullptr;
721 for (auto UI = CI->user_begin(), UE = CI->user_end(); UI != UE;) {
722 ICmpInst *Old = cast<ICmpInst>(*UI++);
723 Value *Cmp =
724 B.CreateICmp(Old->getPredicate(), StrNCmp,
725 ConstantInt::getNullValue(StrNCmp->getType()), "cmp");
726 replaceAllUsesWith(Old, Cmp);
727 }
728 return CI;
729 }
730
731 // See if either input string is a constant string.
732 StringRef SearchStr, ToFindStr;
733 bool HasStr1 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), SearchStr);
734 bool HasStr2 = getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), ToFindStr);
735
736 // fold strstr(x, "") -> x.
737 if (HasStr2 && ToFindStr.empty())
738 return B.CreateBitCast(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getType());
739
740 // If both strings are known, constant fold it.
741 if (HasStr1 && HasStr2) {
742 size_t Offset = SearchStr.find(ToFindStr);
743
744 if (Offset == StringRef::npos) // strstr("foo", "bar") -> null
745 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
746
747 // strstr("abcd", "bc") -> gep((char*)"abcd", 1)
748 Value *Result = castToCStr(CI->getArgOperand(0), B);
749 Result =
750 B.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(B.getInt8Ty(), Result, Offset, "strstr");
751 return B.CreateBitCast(Result, CI->getType());
752 }
753
754 // fold strstr(x, "y") -> strchr(x, 'y').
755 if (HasStr2 && ToFindStr.size() == 1) {
756 Value *StrChr = emitStrChr(CI->getArgOperand(0), ToFindStr[0], B, TLI);
757 return StrChr ? B.CreateBitCast(StrChr, CI->getType()) : nullptr;
758 }
759 return nullptr;
760}
761
762Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemChr(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
763 Value *SrcStr = CI->getArgOperand(0);
764 ConstantInt *CharC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(1));
765 ConstantInt *LenC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(2));
766
767 // memchr(x, y, 0) -> null
768 if (LenC && LenC->isZero())
769 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
770
771 // From now on we need at least constant length and string.
772 StringRef Str;
773 if (!LenC || !getConstantStringInfo(SrcStr, Str, 0, /*TrimAtNul=*/false))
774 return nullptr;
775
776 // Truncate the string to LenC. If Str is smaller than LenC we will still only
777 // scan the string, as reading past the end of it is undefined and we can just
778 // return null if we don't find the char.
779 Str = Str.substr(0, LenC->getZExtValue());
780
781 // If the char is variable but the input str and length are not we can turn
782 // this memchr call into a simple bit field test. Of course this only works
783 // when the return value is only checked against null.
784 //
785 // It would be really nice to reuse switch lowering here but we can't change
786 // the CFG at this point.
787 //
788 // memchr("\r\n", C, 2) != nullptr -> (1 << C & ((1 << '\r') | (1 << '\n')))
789 // != 0
790 // after bounds check.
791 if (!CharC && !Str.empty() && isOnlyUsedInZeroEqualityComparison(CI)) {
792 unsigned char Max =
793 *std::max_element(reinterpret_cast<const unsigned char *>(Str.begin()),
794 reinterpret_cast<const unsigned char *>(Str.end()));
795
796 // Make sure the bit field we're about to create fits in a register on the
797 // target.
798 // FIXME: On a 64 bit architecture this prevents us from using the
799 // interesting range of alpha ascii chars. We could do better by emitting
800 // two bitfields or shifting the range by 64 if no lower chars are used.
801 if (!DL.fitsInLegalInteger(Max + 1))
802 return nullptr;
803
804 // For the bit field use a power-of-2 type with at least 8 bits to avoid
805 // creating unnecessary illegal types.
806 unsigned char Width = NextPowerOf2(std::max((unsigned char)7, Max));
807
808 // Now build the bit field.
809 APInt Bitfield(Width, 0);
810 for (char C : Str)
811 Bitfield.setBit((unsigned char)C);
812 Value *BitfieldC = B.getInt(Bitfield);
813
814 // Adjust width of "C" to the bitfield width, then mask off the high bits.
815 Value *C = B.CreateZExtOrTrunc(CI->getArgOperand(1), BitfieldC->getType());
816 C = B.CreateAnd(C, B.getIntN(Width, 0xFF));
817
818 // First check that the bit field access is within bounds.
819 Value *Bounds = B.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT, C, B.getIntN(Width, Width),
820 "memchr.bounds");
821
822 // Create code that checks if the given bit is set in the field.
823 Value *Shl = B.CreateShl(B.getIntN(Width, 1ULL), C);
824 Value *Bits = B.CreateIsNotNull(B.CreateAnd(Shl, BitfieldC), "memchr.bits");
825
826 // Finally merge both checks and cast to pointer type. To avoid
827 // materialising a nonsense pointer value, we select either a null or the
828 // source string and hope that later bits of instcombine will fold the two
829 // compares.
830 Value *Result = B.CreateAnd(Bounds, Bits, "memchr");
831 return B.CreateSelect(B.CreateIsNull(Result),
832 Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType()), SrcStr);
833 }
834
835 // Check if all arguments are constants. If so, we can constant fold.
836 if (!CharC)
837 return nullptr;
838
839 // Compute the offset.
840 size_t I = Str.find(CharC->getSExtValue() & 0xFF);
841 if (I == StringRef::npos) // Didn't find the char. memchr returns null.
842 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
843
844 // memchr(s+n,c,l) -> gep(s+n+i,c)
845 return B.CreateGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), SrcStr, B.getInt64(I), "memchr");
846}
847
848static Value *optimizeMemCmpConstantSize(CallInst *CI, Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
849 uint64_t Len, IRBuilder<> &B,
850 const DataLayout &DL) {
851 if (Len == 0) // memcmp(s1,s2,0) -> 0
852 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
853
854 // memcmp(S1,S2,1) -> *(unsigned char*)LHS - *(unsigned char*)RHS
855 if (Len == 1) {
856 Value *LHSV =
857 B.CreateZExt(B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), castToCStr(LHS, B), "lhsc"),
858 CI->getType(), "lhsv");
859 Value *RHSV =
860 B.CreateZExt(B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(), castToCStr(RHS, B), "rhsc"),
861 CI->getType(), "rhsv");
862 return B.CreateSub(LHSV, RHSV, "chardiff");
863 }
864
865 // memcmp(S1,S2,N/8)==0 -> (*(intN_t*)S1 != *(intN_t*)S2)==0
866 // TODO: The case where both inputs are constants does not need to be limited
867 // to legal integers or equality comparison. See block below this.
868 if (DL.isLegalInteger(Len * 8) && isOnlyUsedInZeroEqualityComparison(CI)) {
869 IntegerType *IntType = IntegerType::get(CI->getContext(), Len * 8);
870 unsigned PrefAlignment = DL.getPrefTypeAlignment(IntType);
871
872 // First, see if we can fold either argument to a constant.
873 Value *LHSV = nullptr;
874 if (auto *LHSC = dyn_cast<Constant>(LHS)) {
875 unsigned AS = LHSC->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
876 LHSC = ConstantExpr::getBitCast(LHSC, IntType->getPointerTo(AS));
877 LHSV = ConstantFoldLoadFromConstPtr(LHSC, IntType, DL);
878 }
879 Value *RHSV = nullptr;
880 if (auto *RHSC = dyn_cast<Constant>(RHS)) {
881 unsigned AS = RHSC->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
882 RHSC = ConstantExpr::getBitCast(RHSC, IntType->getPointerTo(AS));
883 RHSV = ConstantFoldLoadFromConstPtr(RHSC, IntType, DL);
884 }
885
886 // Don't generate unaligned loads. If either source is constant data,
887 // alignment doesn't matter for that source because there is no load.
888 if ((LHSV || getKnownAlignment(LHS, DL, CI) >= PrefAlignment) &&
889 (RHSV || getKnownAlignment(RHS, DL, CI) >= PrefAlignment)) {
890 if (!LHSV) {
891 Type *LHSPtrTy =
892 IntType->getPointerTo(LHS->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace());
893 LHSV = B.CreateLoad(IntType, B.CreateBitCast(LHS, LHSPtrTy), "lhsv");
894 }
895 if (!RHSV) {
896 Type *RHSPtrTy =
897 IntType->getPointerTo(RHS->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace());
898 RHSV = B.CreateLoad(IntType, B.CreateBitCast(RHS, RHSPtrTy), "rhsv");
899 }
900 return B.CreateZExt(B.CreateICmpNE(LHSV, RHSV), CI->getType(), "memcmp");
901 }
902 }
903
904 // Constant folding: memcmp(x, y, Len) -> constant (all arguments are const).
905 // TODO: This is limited to i8 arrays.
906 StringRef LHSStr, RHSStr;
907 if (getConstantStringInfo(LHS, LHSStr) &&
908 getConstantStringInfo(RHS, RHSStr)) {
909 // Make sure we're not reading out-of-bounds memory.
910 if (Len > LHSStr.size() || Len > RHSStr.size())
911 return nullptr;
912 // Fold the memcmp and normalize the result. This way we get consistent
913 // results across multiple platforms.
914 uint64_t Ret = 0;
915 int Cmp = memcmp(LHSStr.data(), RHSStr.data(), Len);
916 if (Cmp < 0)
917 Ret = -1;
918 else if (Cmp > 0)
919 Ret = 1;
920 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Ret);
921 }
922 return nullptr;
923}

925// Most simplifications for memcmp also apply to bcmp.
926Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemCmpBCmpCommon(CallInst *CI,
927 IRBuilder<> &B) {
928 Value *LHS = CI->getArgOperand(0), *RHS = CI->getArgOperand(1);
929 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2);
930
931 if (LHS == RHS) // memcmp(s,s,x) -> 0
932 return Constant::getNullValue(CI->getType());
933
934 // Handle constant lengths.
935 if (ConstantInt *LenC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Size))
936 if (Value *Res = optimizeMemCmpConstantSize(CI, LHS, RHS,
937 LenC->getZExtValue(), B, DL))
938 return Res;
939
940 return nullptr;
941}

943Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemCmp(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
944 if (Value *V = optimizeMemCmpBCmpCommon(CI, B))
945 return V;
946
947 // memcmp(x, y, Len) == 0 -> bcmp(x, y, Len) == 0
948 // `bcmp` can be more efficient than memcmp because it only has to know that
949 // there is a difference, not where it is.
950 if (isOnlyUsedInZeroEqualityComparison(CI) && TLI->has(LibFunc_bcmp)) {
951 Value *LHS = CI->getArgOperand(0);
952 Value *RHS = CI->getArgOperand(1);
953 Value *Size = CI->getArgOperand(2);
954 return emitBCmp(LHS, RHS, Size, B, DL, TLI);
955 }
956
957 return nullptr;
958}

960Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeBCmp(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
961 return optimizeMemCmpBCmpCommon(CI, B);
962}

978/// Fold memset[_chk](malloc(n), 0, n) --> calloc(1, n).
979Value *LibCallSimplifier::foldMallocMemset(CallInst *Memset, IRBuilder<> &B) {
980 // This has to be a memset of zeros (bzero).
981 auto *FillValue = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Memset->getArgOperand(1));
982 if (!FillValue || FillValue->getZExtValue() != 0)
983 return nullptr;
984
985 // TODO: We should handle the case where the malloc has more than one use.
986 // This is necessary to optimize common patterns such as when the result of
987 // the malloc is checked against null or when a memset intrinsic is used in
988 // place of a memset library call.
989 auto *Malloc = dyn_cast<CallInst>(Memset->getArgOperand(0));
990 if (!Malloc || !Malloc->hasOneUse())
991 return nullptr;
992
993 // Is the inner call really malloc()?
994 Function *InnerCallee = Malloc->getCalledFunction();
995 if (!InnerCallee)
996 return nullptr;
997
998 LibFunc Func;
999 if (!TLI->getLibFunc(*InnerCallee, Func) || !TLI->has(Func) ||
1000 Func != LibFunc_malloc)
1001 return nullptr;
1002
1003 // The memset must cover the same number of bytes that are malloc'd.
1004 if (Memset->getArgOperand(2) != Malloc->getArgOperand(0))
1005 return nullptr;
1006
1007 // Replace the malloc with a calloc. We need the data layout to know what the
1008 // actual size of a 'size_t' parameter is.
1009 B.SetInsertPoint(Malloc->getParent(), ++Malloc->getIterator());
1010 const DataLayout &DL = Malloc->getModule()->getDataLayout();
1011 IntegerType *SizeType = DL.getIntPtrType(B.GetInsertBlock()->getContext());
1012 Value *Calloc = emitCalloc(ConstantInt::get(SizeType, 1),
1013 Malloc->getArgOperand(0), Malloc->getAttributes(),
1014 B, *TLI);
1015 if (!Calloc)
1016 return nullptr;
1017
1018 Malloc->replaceAllUsesWith(Calloc);
1019 eraseFromParent(Malloc);
1020
1021 return Calloc;
1022}
1023
1024Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeMemSet(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1025 if (auto *Calloc = foldMallocMemset(CI, B))
1026 return Calloc;
1027
1028 // memset(p, v, n) -> llvm.memset(align 1 p, v, n)
1029 Value *Val = B.CreateIntCast(CI->getArgOperand(1), B.getInt8Ty(), false);
1030 B.CreateMemSet(CI->getArgOperand(0), Val, CI->getArgOperand(2), 1);
1031 return CI->getArgOperand(0);
1032}

1034Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeRealloc(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1035 if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(CI->getArgOperand(0)))
1036 return emitMalloc(CI->getArgOperand(1), B, DL, TLI);
1037
1038 return nullptr;
1039}

1045// Replace a libcall \p CI with a call to intrinsic \p IID
1046static Value *replaceUnaryCall(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B, Intrinsic::ID IID) {
1047 // Propagate fast-math flags from the existing call to the new call.
1048 IRBuilder<>::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B);
1049 B.setFastMathFlags(CI->getFastMathFlags());
1050
1051 Module *M = CI->getModule();
1052 Value *V = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1053 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, IID, CI->getType());
1054 CallInst *NewCall = B.CreateCall(F, V);
1055 NewCall->takeName(CI);
1056 return NewCall;
1057}
1058
1059/// Return a variant of Val with float type.
1060/// Currently this works in two cases: If Val is an FPExtension of a float
1061/// value to something bigger, simply return the operand.
1062/// If Val is a ConstantFP but can be converted to a float ConstantFP without
1063/// loss of precision do so.
1064static Value *valueHasFloatPrecision(Value *Val) {
1065 if (FPExtInst *Cast = dyn_cast<FPExtInst>(Val)) {
1066 Value *Op = Cast->getOperand(0);
1067 if (Op->getType()->isFloatTy())
1068 return Op;
1069 }
1070 if (ConstantFP *Const = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Val)) {
1071 APFloat F = Const->getValueAPF();
1072 bool losesInfo;
1073 (void)F.convert(APFloat::IEEEsingle(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven,
1074 &losesInfo);
1075 if (!losesInfo)
1076 return ConstantFP::get(Const->getContext(), F);
1077 }
1078 return nullptr;
1079}
1080
1081/// Shrink double -> float functions.
1082static Value *optimizeDoubleFP(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B,
1083 bool isBinary, bool isPrecise = false) {
1084 Function *CalleeFn = CI->getCalledFunction();
1085 if (!CI->getType()->isDoubleTy() || !CalleeFn)
1086 return nullptr;
1087
1088 // If not all the uses of the function are converted to float, then bail out.
1089 // This matters if the precision of the result is more important than the
1090 // precision of the arguments.
1091 if (isPrecise)
1092 for (User *U : CI->users()) {
1093 FPTruncInst *Cast = dyn_cast<FPTruncInst>(U);
1094 if (!Cast || !Cast->getType()->isFloatTy())
1095 return nullptr;
1096 }
1097
1098 // If this is something like 'g((double) float)', convert to 'gf(float)'.
1099 Value *V[2];
1100 V[0] = valueHasFloatPrecision(CI->getArgOperand(0));
1101 V[1] = isBinary ? valueHasFloatPrecision(CI->getArgOperand(1)) : nullptr;
1102 if (!V[0] || (isBinary && !V[1]))
1103 return nullptr;
1104
1105 StringRef CalleeNm = CalleeFn->getName();
1106 AttributeList CalleeAt = CalleeFn->getAttributes();
1107 bool CalleeIn = CalleeFn->isIntrinsic();
1108
1109 // If call isn't an intrinsic, check that it isn't within a function with the
1110 // same name as the float version of this call, otherwise the result is an
1111 // infinite loop. For example, from MinGW-w64:
1112 //
1113 // float expf(float val) { return (float) exp((double) val); }
1114 if (!CalleeIn) {
1115 const Function *Fn = CI->getFunction();
1116 StringRef FnName = Fn->getName();
1117 if (FnName.back() == 'f' &&
1118 FnName.size() == (CalleeNm.size() + 1) &&
1119 FnName.startswith(CalleeNm))
1120 return nullptr;
1121 }
1122
1123 // Propagate the math semantics from the current function to the new function.
1124 IRBuilder<>::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B);
1125 B.setFastMathFlags(CI->getFastMathFlags());
1126
1127 // g((double) float) -> (double) gf(float)
1128 Value *R;
1129 if (CalleeIn) {
1130 Module *M = CI->getModule();
1131 Intrinsic::ID IID = CalleeFn->getIntrinsicID();
1132 Function *Fn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, IID, B.getFloatTy());
1133 R = isBinary ? B.CreateCall(Fn, V) : B.CreateCall(Fn, V[0]);
1134 }
1135 else
1136 R = isBinary ? emitBinaryFloatFnCall(V[0], V[1], CalleeNm, B, CalleeAt)
1137 : emitUnaryFloatFnCall(V[0], CalleeNm, B, CalleeAt);
1138
1139 return B.CreateFPExt(R, B.getDoubleTy());
1140}
1141
1142/// Shrink double -> float for unary functions.
1143static Value *optimizeUnaryDoubleFP(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B,
1144 bool isPrecise = false) {
1145 return optimizeDoubleFP(CI, B, false, isPrecise);
1146}
1147
1148/// Shrink double -> float for binary functions.
1149static Value *optimizeBinaryDoubleFP(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B,
1150 bool isPrecise = false) {
1151 return optimizeDoubleFP(CI, B, true, isPrecise);
1152}

1154// cabs(z) -> sqrt((creal(z)*creal(z)) + (cimag(z)*cimag(z)))
1155Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeCAbs(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1156 if (!CI->isFast())
1157 return nullptr;
1158
1159 // Propagate fast-math flags from the existing call to new instructions.
1160 IRBuilder<>::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B);
1161 B.setFastMathFlags(CI->getFastMathFlags());
1162
1163 Value *Real, *Imag;
1164 if (CI->getNumArgOperands() == 1) {
1165 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1166 assert(Op->getType()->isArrayTy() && "Unexpected signature for cabs!");
1167 Real = B.CreateExtractValue(Op, 0, "real");
1168 Imag = B.CreateExtractValue(Op, 1, "imag");
1169 } else {
1170 assert(CI->getNumArgOperands() == 2 && "Unexpected signature for cabs!");
1171 Real = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1172 Imag = CI->getArgOperand(1);
1173 }
1174
1175 Value *RealReal = B.CreateFMul(Real, Real);
1176 Value *ImagImag = B.CreateFMul(Imag, Imag);
1177
1178 Function *FSqrt = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI->getModule(), Intrinsic::sqrt,
1179 CI->getType());
1180 return B.CreateCall(FSqrt, B.CreateFAdd(RealReal, ImagImag), "cabs");
1181}
1182
1183static Value *optimizeTrigReflections(CallInst *Call, LibFunc Func,
1184 IRBuilder<> &B) {
1185 if (!isa<FPMathOperator>(Call))
1186 return nullptr;
1187
1188 IRBuilder<>::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B);
1189 B.setFastMathFlags(Call->getFastMathFlags());
1190
1191 // TODO: Can this be shared to also handle LLVM intrinsics?
1192 Value *X;
1193 switch (Func) {
1194 case LibFunc_sin:
1195 case LibFunc_sinf:
1196 case LibFunc_sinl:
1197 case LibFunc_tan:
1198 case LibFunc_tanf:
1199 case LibFunc_tanl:
1200 // sin(-X) --> -sin(X)
1201 // tan(-X) --> -tan(X)
1202 if (match(Call->getArgOperand(0), m_OneUse(m_FNeg(m_Value(X)))))
1203 return B.CreateFNeg(B.CreateCall(Call->getCalledFunction(), X));
1204 break;
1205 case LibFunc_cos:
1206 case LibFunc_cosf:
1207 case LibFunc_cosl:
1208 // cos(-X) --> cos(X)
1209 if (match(Call->getArgOperand(0), m_FNeg(m_Value(X))))
1210 return B.CreateCall(Call->getCalledFunction(), X, "cos");
1211 break;
1212 default:
1213 break;
1214 }
1215 return nullptr;
1216}
1217
1218static Value *getPow(Value *InnerChain[33], unsigned Exp, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1219 // Multiplications calculated using Addition Chains.
1220 // Refer: http://wwwhomes.uni-bielefeld.de/achim/addition_chain.html
1221
1222 assert(Exp != 0 && "Incorrect exponent 0 not handled");
1223
1224 if (InnerChain[Exp])
1225 return InnerChain[Exp];
1226
1227 static const unsigned AddChain[33][2] = {
1228 {0, 0}, // Unused.
1229 {0, 0}, // Unused (base case = pow1).
1230 {1, 1}, // Unused (pre-computed).
1231 {1, 2}, {2, 2}, {2, 3}, {3, 3}, {2, 5}, {4, 4},
1232 {1, 8}, {5, 5}, {1, 10}, {6, 6}, {4, 9}, {7, 7},
1233 {3, 12}, {8, 8}, {8, 9}, {2, 16}, {1, 18}, {10, 10},
1234 {6, 15}, {11, 11}, {3, 20}, {12, 12}, {8, 17}, {13, 13},
1235 {3, 24}, {14, 14}, {4, 25}, {15, 15}, {3, 28}, {16, 16},
1236 };
1237
1238 InnerChain[Exp] = B.CreateFMul(getPow(InnerChain, AddChain[Exp][0], B),
1239 getPow(InnerChain, AddChain[Exp][1], B));
1240 return InnerChain[Exp];
1241}
1242
1243/// Use exp{,2}(x * y) for pow(exp{,2}(x), y);
1244/// exp2(n * x) for pow(2.0 ** n, x); exp10(x) for pow(10.0, x).
1245Value *LibCallSimplifier::replacePowWithExp(CallInst *Pow, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1246 Value *Base = Pow->getArgOperand(0), *Expo = Pow->getArgOperand(1);
1247 AttributeList Attrs = Pow->getCalledFunction()->getAttributes();
1248 Module *Mod = Pow->getModule();
1249 Type *Ty = Pow->getType();
1250 bool Ignored;
1251
1252 // Evaluate special cases related to a nested function as the base.
1253
1254 // pow(exp(x), y) -> exp(x * y)
1255 // pow(exp2(x), y) -> exp2(x * y)
1256 // If exp{,2}() is used only once, it is better to fold two transcendental
1257 // math functions into one. If used again, exp{,2}() would still have to be
1258 // called with the original argument, then keep both original transcendental
1259 // functions. However, this transformation is only safe with fully relaxed
1260 // math semantics, since, besides rounding differences, it changes overflow
1261 // and underflow behavior quite dramatically. For example:
1262 // pow(exp(1000), 0.001) = pow(inf, 0.001) = inf
1263 // Whereas:
1264 // exp(1000 * 0.001) = exp(1)
1265 // TODO: Loosen the requirement for fully relaxed math semantics.
1266 // TODO: Handle exp10() when more targets have it available.
1267 CallInst *BaseFn = dyn_cast<CallInst>(Base);
1268 if (BaseFn && BaseFn->hasOneUse() && BaseFn->isFast() && Pow->isFast()) {
1269 LibFunc LibFn;
1270
1271 Function *CalleeFn = BaseFn->getCalledFunction();
1272 if (CalleeFn &&
1273 TLI->getLibFunc(CalleeFn->getName(), LibFn) && TLI->has(LibFn)) {
1274 StringRef ExpName;
1275 Intrinsic::ID ID;
1276 Value *ExpFn;
1277 LibFunc LibFnFloat;
1278 LibFunc LibFnDouble;
1279 LibFunc LibFnLongDouble;
1280
1281 switch (LibFn) {
1282 default:
1283 return nullptr;
1284 case LibFunc_expf: case LibFunc_exp: case LibFunc_expl:
1285 ExpName = TLI->getName(LibFunc_exp);
1286 ID = Intrinsic::exp;
1287 LibFnFloat = LibFunc_expf;
1288 LibFnDouble = LibFunc_exp;
1289 LibFnLongDouble = LibFunc_expl;
1290 break;
1291 case LibFunc_exp2f: case LibFunc_exp2: case LibFunc_exp2l:
1292 ExpName = TLI->getName(LibFunc_exp2);
1293 ID = Intrinsic::exp2;
1294 LibFnFloat = LibFunc_exp2f;
1295 LibFnDouble = LibFunc_exp2;
1296 LibFnLongDouble = LibFunc_exp2l;
1297 break;
1298 }
1299
1300 // Create new exp{,2}() with the product as its argument.
1301 Value *FMul = B.CreateFMul(BaseFn->getArgOperand(0), Expo, "mul");
1302 ExpFn = BaseFn->doesNotAccessMemory()
1303 ? B.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, ID, Ty),
1304 FMul, ExpName)
1305 : emitUnaryFloatFnCall(FMul, TLI, LibFnDouble, LibFnFloat,
1306 LibFnLongDouble, B,
1307 BaseFn->getAttributes());
1308
1309 // Since the new exp{,2}() is different from the original one, dead code
1310 // elimination cannot be trusted to remove it, since it may have side
1311 // effects (e.g., errno). When the only consumer for the original
1312 // exp{,2}() is pow(), then it has to be explicitly erased.
1313 BaseFn->replaceAllUsesWith(ExpFn);
1314 eraseFromParent(BaseFn);
1315
1316 return ExpFn;
1317 }
1318 }
1319
1320 // Evaluate special cases related to a constant base.
1321
1322 const APFloat *BaseF;
1323 if (!match(Pow->getArgOperand(0), m_APFloat(BaseF)))
1324 return nullptr;
1325
1326 // pow(2.0 ** n, x) -> exp2(n * x)
1327 if (hasUnaryFloatFn(TLI, Ty, LibFunc_exp2, LibFunc_exp2f, LibFunc_exp2l)) {
1328 APFloat BaseR = APFloat(1.0);
1329 BaseR.convert(BaseF->getSemantics(), APFloat::rmTowardZero, &Ignored);
1330 BaseR = BaseR / *BaseF;
1331 bool IsInteger = BaseF->isInteger(),
1332 IsReciprocal = BaseR.isInteger();
1333 const APFloat *NF = IsReciprocal ? &BaseR : BaseF;
1334 APSInt NI(64, false);
1335 if ((IsInteger || IsReciprocal) &&
1336 !NF->convertToInteger(NI, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &Ignored) &&
1337 NI > 1 && NI.isPowerOf2()) {
1338 double N = NI.logBase2() * (IsReciprocal ? -1.0 : 1.0);
1339 Value *FMul = B.CreateFMul(Expo, ConstantFP::get(Ty, N), "mul");
1340 if (Pow->doesNotAccessMemory())
1341 return B.CreateCall(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, Intrinsic::exp2, Ty),
1342 FMul, "exp2");
1343 else
1344 return emitUnaryFloatFnCall(FMul, TLI, LibFunc_exp2, LibFunc_exp2f,
1345 LibFunc_exp2l, B, Attrs);
1346 }
1347 }
1348
1349 // pow(10.0, x) -> exp10(x)
1350 // TODO: There is no exp10() intrinsic yet, but some day there shall be one.
1351 if (match(Base, m_SpecificFP(10.0)) &&
1352 hasUnaryFloatFn(TLI, Ty, LibFunc_exp10, LibFunc_exp10f, LibFunc_exp10l))
1353 return emitUnaryFloatFnCall(Expo, TLI, LibFunc_exp10, LibFunc_exp10f,
1354 LibFunc_exp10l, B, Attrs);
1355
1356 return nullptr;
1357}
1358
1359static Value *getSqrtCall(Value *V, AttributeList Attrs, bool NoErrno,
1360 Module *M, IRBuilder<> &B,
1361 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) {
1362 // If errno is never set, then use the intrinsic for sqrt().
1363 if (NoErrno) {
1364 Function *SqrtFn =
1365 Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, Intrinsic::sqrt, V->getType());
1366 return B.CreateCall(SqrtFn, V, "sqrt");
1367 }
1368
1369 // Otherwise, use the libcall for sqrt().
1370 if (hasUnaryFloatFn(TLI, V->getType(), LibFunc_sqrt, LibFunc_sqrtf,
1371 LibFunc_sqrtl))
1372 // TODO: We also should check that the target can in fact lower the sqrt()
1373 // libcall. We currently have no way to ask this question, so we ask if
1374 // the target has a sqrt() libcall, which is not exactly the same.
1375 return emitUnaryFloatFnCall(V, TLI, LibFunc_sqrt, LibFunc_sqrtf,
1376 LibFunc_sqrtl, B, Attrs);
1377
1378 return nullptr;
1379}
1380
1381/// Use square root in place of pow(x, +/-0.5).
1382Value *LibCallSimplifier::replacePowWithSqrt(CallInst *Pow, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1383 Value *Sqrt, *Base = Pow->getArgOperand(0), *Expo = Pow->getArgOperand(1);
1384 AttributeList Attrs = Pow->getCalledFunction()->getAttributes();
1385 Module *Mod = Pow->getModule();
1386 Type *Ty = Pow->getType();
1387
1388 const APFloat *ExpoF;
1389 if (!match(Expo, m_APFloat(ExpoF)) ||
1390 (!ExpoF->isExactlyValue(0.5) && !ExpoF->isExactlyValue(-0.5)))
1391 return nullptr;
1392
1393 Sqrt = getSqrtCall(Base, Attrs, Pow->doesNotAccessMemory(), Mod, B, TLI);
1394 if (!Sqrt)
1395 return nullptr;
1396
1397 // Handle signed zero base by expanding to fabs(sqrt(x)).
1398 if (!Pow->hasNoSignedZeros()) {
1399 Function *FAbsFn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, Intrinsic::fabs, Ty);
1400 Sqrt = B.CreateCall(FAbsFn, Sqrt, "abs");
1401 }
1402
1403 // Handle non finite base by expanding to
1404 // (x == -infinity ? +infinity : sqrt(x)).
1405 if (!Pow->hasNoInfs()) {
1406 Value *PosInf = ConstantFP::getInfinity(Ty),
1407 *NegInf = ConstantFP::getInfinity(Ty, true);
1408 Value *FCmp = B.CreateFCmpOEQ(Base, NegInf, "isinf");
1409 Sqrt = B.CreateSelect(FCmp, PosInf, Sqrt);
1410 }
1411
1412 // If the exponent is negative, then get the reciprocal.
1413 if (ExpoF->isNegative())
1414 Sqrt = B.CreateFDiv(ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0), Sqrt, "reciprocal");
1415
1416 return Sqrt;
1417}
1418
1419Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizePow(CallInst *Pow, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1420 Value *Base = Pow->getArgOperand(0), *Expo = Pow->getArgOperand(1);
1421 Function *Callee = Pow->getCalledFunction();
1422 StringRef Name = Callee->getName();
1423 Type *Ty = Pow->getType();
1424 Value *Shrunk = nullptr;
1425 bool Ignored;
1426
1427 // Bail out if simplifying libcalls to pow() is disabled.
1428 if (!hasUnaryFloatFn(TLI, Ty, LibFunc_pow, LibFunc_powf, LibFunc_powl))
1429 return nullptr;
1430
1431 // Propagate the math semantics from the call to any created instructions.
1432 IRBuilder<>::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B);
1433 B.setFastMathFlags(Pow->getFastMathFlags());
1434
1435 // Shrink pow() to powf() if the arguments are single precision,
1436 // unless the result is expected to be double precision.
1437 if (UnsafeFPShrink &&
1438 Name == TLI->getName(LibFunc_pow) && hasFloatVersion(Name))
1439 Shrunk = optimizeBinaryDoubleFP(Pow, B, true);
1440
1441 // Evaluate special cases related to the base.
1442
1443 // pow(1.0, x) -> 1.0
1444 if (match(Base, m_FPOne()))
1445 return Base;
1446
1447 if (Value *Exp = replacePowWithExp(Pow, B))
1448 return Exp;
1449
1450 // Evaluate special cases related to the exponent.
1451
1452 // pow(x, -1.0) -> 1.0 / x
1453 if (match(Expo, m_SpecificFP(-1.0)))
1454 return B.CreateFDiv(ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0), Base, "reciprocal");
1455
1456 // pow(x, 0.0) -> 1.0
1457 if (match(Expo, m_SpecificFP(0.0)))
1458 return ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0);
1459
1460 // pow(x, 1.0) -> x
1461 if (match(Expo, m_FPOne()))
1462 return Base;
1463
1464 // pow(x, 2.0) -> x * x
1465 if (match(Expo, m_SpecificFP(2.0)))
1466 return B.CreateFMul(Base, Base, "square");
1467
1468 if (Value *Sqrt = replacePowWithSqrt(Pow, B))
1469 return Sqrt;
1470
1471 // pow(x, n) -> x * x * x * ...
1472 const APFloat *ExpoF;
1473 if (Pow->isFast() && match(Expo, m_APFloat(ExpoF))) {
1474 // We limit to a max of 7 multiplications, thus the maximum exponent is 32.
1475 // If the exponent is an integer+0.5 we generate a call to sqrt and an
1476 // additional fmul.
1477 // TODO: This whole transformation should be backend specific (e.g. some
1478 // backends might prefer libcalls or the limit for the exponent might
1479 // be different) and it should also consider optimizing for size.
1480 APFloat LimF(ExpoF->getSemantics(), 33.0),
1481 ExpoA(abs(*ExpoF));
1482 if (ExpoA.compare(LimF) == APFloat::cmpLessThan) {
1483 // This transformation applies to integer or integer+0.5 exponents only.
1484 // For integer+0.5, we create a sqrt(Base) call.
1485 Value *Sqrt = nullptr;
1486 if (!ExpoA.isInteger()) {
1487 APFloat Expo2 = ExpoA;
1488 // To check if ExpoA is an integer + 0.5, we add it to itself. If there
1489 // is no floating point exception and the result is an integer, then
1490 // ExpoA == integer + 0.5
1491 if (Expo2.add(ExpoA, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven) != APFloat::opOK)
1492 return nullptr;
1493
1494 if (!Expo2.isInteger())
1495 return nullptr;
1496
1497 Sqrt =
1498 getSqrtCall(Base, Pow->getCalledFunction()->getAttributes(),
1499 Pow->doesNotAccessMemory(), Pow->getModule(), B, TLI);
1500 }
1501
1502 // We will memoize intermediate products of the Addition Chain.
1503 Value *InnerChain[33] = {nullptr};
1504 InnerChain[1] = Base;
1505 InnerChain[2] = B.CreateFMul(Base, Base, "square");
1506
1507 // We cannot readily convert a non-double type (like float) to a double.
1508 // So we first convert it to something which could be converted to double.
1509 ExpoA.convert(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APFloat::rmTowardZero, &Ignored);
1510 Value *FMul = getPow(InnerChain, ExpoA.convertToDouble(), B);
1511
1512 // Expand pow(x, y+0.5) to pow(x, y) * sqrt(x).
1513 if (Sqrt)
1514 FMul = B.CreateFMul(FMul, Sqrt);
1515
1516 // If the exponent is negative, then get the reciprocal.
1517 if (ExpoF->isNegative())
1518 FMul = B.CreateFDiv(ConstantFP::get(Ty, 1.0), FMul, "reciprocal");
1519
1520 return FMul;
1521 }
1522 }
1523
1524 return Shrunk;
1525}
1526
1527Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeExp2(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1528 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
1529 Value *Ret = nullptr;
1530 StringRef Name = Callee->getName();
1531 if (UnsafeFPShrink && Name == "exp2" && hasFloatVersion(Name))
1532 Ret = optimizeUnaryDoubleFP(CI, B, true);
1533
1534 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1535 // Turn exp2(sitofp(x)) -> ldexp(1.0, sext(x)) if sizeof(x) <= 32
1536 // Turn exp2(uitofp(x)) -> ldexp(1.0, zext(x)) if sizeof(x) < 32
1537 LibFunc LdExp = LibFunc_ldexpl;
1538 if (Op->getType()->isFloatTy())
1539 LdExp = LibFunc_ldexpf;
1540 else if (Op->getType()->isDoubleTy())
1541 LdExp = LibFunc_ldexp;
1542
1543 if (TLI->has(LdExp)) {
1544 Value *LdExpArg = nullptr;
1545 if (SIToFPInst *OpC = dyn_cast<SIToFPInst>(Op)) {
1546 if (OpC->getOperand(0)->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() <= 32)
1547 LdExpArg = B.CreateSExt(OpC->getOperand(0), B.getInt32Ty());
1548 } else if (UIToFPInst *OpC = dyn_cast<UIToFPInst>(Op)) {
1549 if (OpC->getOperand(0)->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() < 32)
1550 LdExpArg = B.CreateZExt(OpC->getOperand(0), B.getInt32Ty());
1551 }
1552
1553 if (LdExpArg) {
1554 Constant *One = ConstantFP::get(CI->getContext(), APFloat(1.0f));
1555 if (!Op->getType()->isFloatTy())
1556 One = ConstantExpr::getFPExtend(One, Op->getType());
1557
1558 Module *M = CI->getModule();
1559 FunctionCallee NewCallee = M->getOrInsertFunction(
1560 TLI->getName(LdExp), Op->getType(), Op->getType(), B.getInt32Ty());
1561 CallInst *CI = B.CreateCall(NewCallee, {One, LdExpArg});
1562 if (const Function *F = dyn_cast<Function>(Callee->stripPointerCasts()))
1563 CI->setCallingConv(F->getCallingConv());
1564
1565 return CI;
1566 }
1567 }
1568 return Ret;
1569}
1570
1571Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFMinFMax(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1572 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
1573 // If we can shrink the call to a float function rather than a double
1574 // function, do that first.
1575 StringRef Name = Callee->getName();
1576 if ((Name == "fmin" || Name == "fmax") && hasFloatVersion(Name))
1577 if (Value *Ret = optimizeBinaryDoubleFP(CI, B))
1578 return Ret;
1579
1580 IRBuilder<>::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B);
1581 FastMathFlags FMF;
1582 if (CI->isFast()) {
1583 // If the call is 'fast', then anything we create here will also be 'fast'.
1584 FMF.setFast();
1585 } else {
1586 // At a minimum, no-nans-fp-math must be true.
1587 if (!CI->hasNoNaNs())
1588 return nullptr;
1589 // No-signed-zeros is implied by the definitions of fmax/fmin themselves:
1590 // "Ideally, fmax would be sensitive to the sign of zero, for example
1591 // fmax(-0. 0, +0. 0) would return +0; however, implementation in software
1592 // might be impractical."
1593 FMF.setNoSignedZeros();
1594 FMF.setNoNaNs();
1595 }
1596 B.setFastMathFlags(FMF);
1597
1598 // We have a relaxed floating-point environment. We can ignore NaN-handling
1599 // and transform to a compare and select. We do not have to consider errno or
1600 // exceptions, because fmin/fmax do not have those.
1601 Value *Op0 = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1602 Value *Op1 = CI->getArgOperand(1);
1603 Value *Cmp = Callee->getName().startswith("fmin") ?
1604 B.CreateFCmpOLT(Op0, Op1) : B.CreateFCmpOGT(Op0, Op1);
1605 return B.CreateSelect(Cmp, Op0, Op1);
1606}
1607
1608Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeLog(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1609 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
1610 Value *Ret = nullptr;
1611 StringRef Name = Callee->getName();
1612 if (UnsafeFPShrink && hasFloatVersion(Name))
1613 Ret = optimizeUnaryDoubleFP(CI, B, true);
1614
1615 if (!CI->isFast())
1616 return Ret;
1617 Value *Op1 = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1618 auto *OpC = dyn_cast<CallInst>(Op1);
1619
1620 // The earlier call must also be 'fast' in order to do these transforms.
1621 if (!OpC || !OpC->isFast())
1622 return Ret;
1623
1624 // log(pow(x,y)) -> y*log(x)
1625 // This is only applicable to log, log2, log10.
1626 if (Name != "log" && Name != "log2" && Name != "log10")
1627 return Ret;
1628
1629 IRBuilder<>::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B);
1630 FastMathFlags FMF;
1631 FMF.setFast();
1632 B.setFastMathFlags(FMF);
1633
1634 LibFunc Func;
1635 Function *F = OpC->getCalledFunction();
1636 if (F && ((TLI->getLibFunc(F->getName(), Func) && TLI->has(Func) &&
1637 Func == LibFunc_pow) || F->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::pow))
1638 return B.CreateFMul(OpC->getArgOperand(1),
1639 emitUnaryFloatFnCall(OpC->getOperand(0), Callee->getName(), B,
1640 Callee->getAttributes()), "mul");
1641
1642 // log(exp2(y)) -> y*log(2)
1643 if (F && Name == "log" && TLI->getLibFunc(F->getName(), Func) &&
1644 TLI->has(Func) && Func == LibFunc_exp2)
1645 return B.CreateFMul(
1646 OpC->getArgOperand(0),
1647 emitUnaryFloatFnCall(ConstantFP::get(CI->getType(), 2.0),
1648 Callee->getName(), B, Callee->getAttributes()),
1649 "logmul");
1650 return Ret;
1651}
1652
1653Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSqrt(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1654 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
1655 Value *Ret = nullptr;
1656 // TODO: Once we have a way (other than checking for the existince of the
1657 // libcall) to tell whether our target can lower @llvm.sqrt, relax the
1658 // condition below.
1659 if (TLI->has(LibFunc_sqrtf) && (Callee->getName() == "sqrt" ||
1660 Callee->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::sqrt))
1661 Ret = optimizeUnaryDoubleFP(CI, B, true);
1662
1663 if (!CI->isFast())
1664 return Ret;
1665
1666 Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(CI->getArgOperand(0));
1667 if (!I || I->getOpcode() != Instruction::FMul || !I->isFast())
1668 return Ret;
1669
1670 // We're looking for a repeated factor in a multiplication tree,
1671 // so we can do this fold: sqrt(x * x) -> fabs(x);
1672 // or this fold: sqrt((x * x) * y) -> fabs(x) * sqrt(y).
1673 Value *Op0 = I->getOperand(0);
1674 Value *Op1 = I->getOperand(1);
1675 Value *RepeatOp = nullptr;
1676 Value *OtherOp = nullptr;
1677 if (Op0 == Op1) {
1678 // Simple match: the operands of the multiply are identical.
1679 RepeatOp = Op0;
1680 } else {
1681 // Look for a more complicated pattern: one of the operands is itself
1682 // a multiply, so search for a common factor in that multiply.
1683 // Note: We don't bother looking any deeper than this first level or for
1684 // variations of this pattern because instcombine's visitFMUL and/or the
1685 // reassociation pass should give us this form.
1686 Value *OtherMul0, *OtherMul1;
1687 if (match(Op0, m_FMul(m_Value(OtherMul0), m_Value(OtherMul1)))) {
1688 // Pattern: sqrt((x * y) * z)
1689 if (OtherMul0 == OtherMul1 && cast<Instruction>(Op0)->isFast()) {
1690 // Matched: sqrt((x * x) * z)
1691 RepeatOp = OtherMul0;
1692 OtherOp = Op1;
1693 }
1694 }
1695 }
1696 if (!RepeatOp)
1697 return Ret;
1698
1699 // Fast math flags for any created instructions should match the sqrt
1700 // and multiply.
1701 IRBuilder<>::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(B);
1702 B.setFastMathFlags(I->getFastMathFlags());
1703
1704 // If we found a repeated factor, hoist it out of the square root and
1705 // replace it with the fabs of that factor.
1706 Module *M = Callee->getParent();
1707 Type *ArgType = I->getType();
1708 Function *Fabs = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, Intrinsic::fabs, ArgType);
1709 Value *FabsCall = B.CreateCall(Fabs, RepeatOp, "fabs");
1710 if (OtherOp) {
1711 // If we found a non-repeated factor, we still need to get its square
1712 // root. We then multiply that by the value that was simplified out
1713 // of the square root calculation.
1714 Function *Sqrt = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, Intrinsic::sqrt, ArgType);
1715 Value *SqrtCall = B.CreateCall(Sqrt, OtherOp, "sqrt");
1716 return B.CreateFMul(FabsCall, SqrtCall);
1717 }
1718 return FabsCall;
1719}
1720
1721// TODO: Generalize to handle any trig function and its inverse.
1722Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeTan(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1723 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
1724 Value *Ret = nullptr;
1725 StringRef Name = Callee->getName();
1726 if (UnsafeFPShrink && Name == "tan" && hasFloatVersion(Name))
1727 Ret = optimizeUnaryDoubleFP(CI, B, true);
1728
1729 Value *Op1 = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1730 auto *OpC = dyn_cast<CallInst>(Op1);
1731 if (!OpC)
1732 return Ret;
1733
1734 // Both calls must be 'fast' in order to remove them.
1735 if (!CI->isFast() || !OpC->isFast())
1736 return Ret;
1737
1738 // tan(atan(x)) -> x
1739 // tanf(atanf(x)) -> x
1740 // tanl(atanl(x)) -> x
1741 LibFunc Func;
1742 Function *F = OpC->getCalledFunction();
1743 if (F && TLI->getLibFunc(F->getName(), Func) && TLI->has(Func) &&
1744 ((Func == LibFunc_atan && Callee->getName() == "tan") ||
1745 (Func == LibFunc_atanf && Callee->getName() == "tanf") ||
1746 (Func == LibFunc_atanl && Callee->getName() == "tanl")))
1747 Ret = OpC->getArgOperand(0);
1748 return Ret;
1749}
1750
1751static bool isTrigLibCall(CallInst *CI) {
1752 // We can only hope to do anything useful if we can ignore things like errno
1753 // and floating-point exceptions.
1754 // We already checked the prototype.
1755 return CI->hasFnAttr(Attribute::NoUnwind) &&
1756 CI->hasFnAttr(Attribute::ReadNone);
1757}
1758
1759static void insertSinCosCall(IRBuilder<> &B, Function *OrigCallee, Value *Arg,
1760 bool UseFloat, Value *&Sin, Value *&Cos,
1761 Value *&SinCos) {
1762 Type *ArgTy = Arg->getType();
1763 Type *ResTy;
1764 StringRef Name;
1765
1766 Triple T(OrigCallee->getParent()->getTargetTriple());
1767 if (UseFloat) {
1768 Name = "__sincospif_stret";
1769
1770 assert(T.getArch() != Triple::x86 && "x86 messy and unsupported for now");
1771 // x86_64 can't use {float, float} since that would be returned in both
1772 // xmm0 and xmm1, which isn't what a real struct would do.
1773 ResTy = T.getArch() == Triple::x86_64
1774 ? static_cast<Type *>(VectorType::get(ArgTy, 2))
1775 : static_cast<Type *>(StructType::get(ArgTy, ArgTy));
1776 } else {
1777 Name = "__sincospi_stret";
1778 ResTy = StructType::get(ArgTy, ArgTy);
1779 }
1780
1781 Module *M = OrigCallee->getParent();
1782 FunctionCallee Callee =
1783 M->getOrInsertFunction(Name, OrigCallee->getAttributes(), ResTy, ArgTy);
1784
1785 if (Instruction *ArgInst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Arg)) {
1786 // If the argument is an instruction, it must dominate all uses so put our
1787 // sincos call there.
1788 B.SetInsertPoint(ArgInst->getParent(), ++ArgInst->getIterator());
1789 } else {
1790 // Otherwise (e.g. for a constant) the beginning of the function is as
1791 // good a place as any.
1792 BasicBlock &EntryBB = B.GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->getEntryBlock();
1793 B.SetInsertPoint(&EntryBB, EntryBB.begin());
1794 }
1795
1796 SinCos = B.CreateCall(Callee, Arg, "sincospi");
1797
1798 if (SinCos->getType()->isStructTy()) {
1799 Sin = B.CreateExtractValue(SinCos, 0, "sinpi");
1800 Cos = B.CreateExtractValue(SinCos, 1, "cospi");
1801 } else {
1802 Sin = B.CreateExtractElement(SinCos, ConstantInt::get(B.getInt32Ty(), 0),
1803 "sinpi");
1804 Cos = B.CreateExtractElement(SinCos, ConstantInt::get(B.getInt32Ty(), 1),
1805 "cospi");
1806 }
1807}
1808
1809Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSinCosPi(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1810 // Make sure the prototype is as expected, otherwise the rest of the
1811 // function is probably invalid and likely to abort.
1812 if (!isTrigLibCall(CI))
1813 return nullptr;
1814
1815 Value *Arg = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1816 SmallVector<CallInst *, 1> SinCalls;
1817 SmallVector<CallInst *, 1> CosCalls;
1818 SmallVector<CallInst *, 1> SinCosCalls;
1819
1820 bool IsFloat = Arg->getType()->isFloatTy();
1821
1822 // Look for all compatible sinpi, cospi and sincospi calls with the same
1823 // argument. If there are enough (in some sense) we can make the
1824 // substitution.
1825 Function *F = CI->getFunction();
1826 for (User *U : Arg->users())
1827 classifyArgUse(U, F, IsFloat, SinCalls, CosCalls, SinCosCalls);
1828
1829 // It's only worthwhile if both sinpi and cospi are actually used.
1830 if (SinCosCalls.empty() && (SinCalls.empty() || CosCalls.empty()))
1831 return nullptr;
1832
1833 Value *Sin, *Cos, *SinCos;
1834 insertSinCosCall(B, CI->getCalledFunction(), Arg, IsFloat, Sin, Cos, SinCos);
1835
1836 auto replaceTrigInsts = [this](SmallVectorImpl<CallInst *> &Calls,
1837 Value *Res) {
1838 for (CallInst *C : Calls)
1839 replaceAllUsesWith(C, Res);
1840 };
1841
1842 replaceTrigInsts(SinCalls, Sin);
1843 replaceTrigInsts(CosCalls, Cos);
1844 replaceTrigInsts(SinCosCalls, SinCos);
1845
1846 return nullptr;
1847}
1848
1849void LibCallSimplifier::classifyArgUse(
1850 Value *Val, Function *F, bool IsFloat,
1851 SmallVectorImpl<CallInst *> &SinCalls,
1852 SmallVectorImpl<CallInst *> &CosCalls,
1853 SmallVectorImpl<CallInst *> &SinCosCalls) {
1854 CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(Val);
1855
1856 if (!CI)
1857 return;
1858
1859 // Don't consider calls in other functions.
1860 if (CI->getFunction() != F)
1861 return;
1862
1863 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
1864 LibFunc Func;
1865 if (!Callee || !TLI->getLibFunc(*Callee, Func) || !TLI->has(Func) ||
1866 !isTrigLibCall(CI))
1867 return;
1868
1869 if (IsFloat) {
1870 if (Func == LibFunc_sinpif)
1871 SinCalls.push_back(CI);
1872 else if (Func == LibFunc_cospif)
1873 CosCalls.push_back(CI);
1874 else if (Func == LibFunc_sincospif_stret)
1875 SinCosCalls.push_back(CI);
1876 } else {
1877 if (Func == LibFunc_sinpi)
1878 SinCalls.push_back(CI);
1879 else if (Func == LibFunc_cospi)
1880 CosCalls.push_back(CI);
1881 else if (Func == LibFunc_sincospi_stret)
1882 SinCosCalls.push_back(CI);
1883 }
1884}

1889
1890Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFFS(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1891 // ffs(x) -> x != 0 ? (i32)llvm.cttz(x)+1 : 0
1892 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1893 Type *ArgType = Op->getType();
1894 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI->getCalledFunction()->getParent(),
1895 Intrinsic::cttz, ArgType);
1896 Value *V = B.CreateCall(F, {Op, B.getTrue()}, "cttz");
1897 V = B.CreateAdd(V, ConstantInt::get(V->getType(), 1));
1898 V = B.CreateIntCast(V, B.getInt32Ty(), false);
1899
1900 Value *Cond = B.CreateICmpNE(Op, Constant::getNullValue(ArgType));
1901 return B.CreateSelect(Cond, V, B.getInt32(0));
1902}
1903
1904Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFls(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1905 // fls(x) -> (i32)(sizeInBits(x) - llvm.ctlz(x, false))
1906 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1907 Type *ArgType = Op->getType();
1908 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(CI->getCalledFunction()->getParent(),
1909 Intrinsic::ctlz, ArgType);
1910 Value *V = B.CreateCall(F, {Op, B.getFalse()}, "ctlz");
1911 V = B.CreateSub(ConstantInt::get(V->getType(), ArgType->getIntegerBitWidth()),
1912 V);
1913 return B.CreateIntCast(V, CI->getType(), false);
1914}
1915
1916Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeAbs(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1917 // abs(x) -> x <s 0 ? -x : x
1918 // The negation has 'nsw' because abs of INT_MIN is undefined.
1919 Value *X = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1920 Value *IsNeg = B.CreateICmpSLT(X, Constant::getNullValue(X->getType()));
1921 Value *NegX = B.CreateNSWNeg(X, "neg");
1922 return B.CreateSelect(IsNeg, NegX, X);
1923}
1924
1925Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeIsDigit(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1926 // isdigit(c) -> (c-'0') <u 10
1927 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1928 Op = B.CreateSub(Op, B.getInt32('0'), "isdigittmp");
1929 Op = B.CreateICmpULT(Op, B.getInt32(10), "isdigit");
1930 return B.CreateZExt(Op, CI->getType());
1931}
1932
1933Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeIsAscii(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1934 // isascii(c) -> c <u 128
1935 Value *Op = CI->getArgOperand(0);
1936 Op = B.CreateICmpULT(Op, B.getInt32(128), "isascii");
1937 return B.CreateZExt(Op, CI->getType());
1938}
1939
1940Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeToAscii(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1941 // toascii(c) -> c & 0x7f
1942 return B.CreateAnd(CI->getArgOperand(0),
1943 ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0x7F));
1944}
1945
1946Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeAtoi(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1947 StringRef Str;
1948 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), Str))
1949 return nullptr;
1950
1951 return convertStrToNumber(CI, Str, 10);
1952}
1953
1954Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrtol(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
1955 StringRef Str;
1956 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), Str))
1957 return nullptr;
1958
1959 if (!isa<ConstantPointerNull>(CI->getArgOperand(1)))
1960 return nullptr;
1961
1962 if (ConstantInt *CInt = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(2))) {
1963 return convertStrToNumber(CI, Str, CInt->getSExtValue());
1964 }
1965
1966 return nullptr;
1967}

1969//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1970// Formatting and IO Library Call Optimizations
1971//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1972
1973static bool isReportingError(Function *Callee, CallInst *CI, int StreamArg);
1974
1975Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeErrorReporting(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B,
1976 int StreamArg) {
1977 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
1978 // Error reporting calls should be cold, mark them as such.
1979 // This applies even to non-builtin calls: it is only a hint and applies to
1980 // functions that the frontend might not understand as builtins.
1981
1982 // This heuristic was suggested in:
1983 // Improving Static Branch Prediction in a Compiler
1984 // Brian L. Deitrich, Ben-Chung Cheng, Wen-mei W. Hwu
1985 // Proceedings of PACT'98, Oct. 1998, IEEE
1986 if (!CI->hasFnAttr(Attribute::Cold) &&
1987 isReportingError(Callee, CI, StreamArg)) {
1988 CI->addAttribute(AttributeList::FunctionIndex, Attribute::Cold);
1989 }
1990
1991 return nullptr;
1992}
1993
1994static bool isReportingError(Function *Callee, CallInst *CI, int StreamArg) {
1995 if (!Callee || !Callee->isDeclaration())
1996 return false;
1997
1998 if (StreamArg < 0)
1999 return true;
2000
2001 // These functions might be considered cold, but only if their stream
2002 // argument is stderr.
2003
2004 if (StreamArg >= (int)CI->getNumArgOperands())
2005 return false;
2006 LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(CI->getArgOperand(StreamArg));
2007 if (!LI)
2008 return false;
2009 GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(LI->getPointerOperand());
2010 if (!GV || !GV->isDeclaration())
2011 return false;
2012 return GV->getName() == "stderr";
2013}
2014
2015Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizePrintFString(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2016 // Check for a fixed format string.
2017 StringRef FormatStr;
2018 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(0), FormatStr))
2019 return nullptr;
2020
2021 // Empty format string -> noop.
2022 if (FormatStr.empty()) // Tolerate printf's declared void.
2023 return CI->use_empty() ? (Value *)CI : ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0);
2024
2025 // Do not do any of the following transformations if the printf return value
2026 // is used, in general the printf return value is not compatible with either
2027 // putchar() or puts().
2028 if (!CI->use_empty())
2029 return nullptr;
2030
2031 // printf("x") -> putchar('x'), even for "%" and "%%".
2032 if (FormatStr.size() == 1 || FormatStr == "%%")
2033 return emitPutChar(B.getInt32(FormatStr[0]), B, TLI);
2034
2035 // printf("%s", "a") --> putchar('a')
2036 if (FormatStr == "%s" && CI->getNumArgOperands() > 1) {
2037 StringRef ChrStr;
2038 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getOperand(1), ChrStr))
2039 return nullptr;
2040 if (ChrStr.size() != 1)
2041 return nullptr;
2042 return emitPutChar(B.getInt32(ChrStr[0]), B, TLI);
2043 }
2044
2045 // printf("foo\n") --> puts("foo")
2046 if (FormatStr[FormatStr.size() - 1] == '\n' &&
2047 FormatStr.find('%') == StringRef::npos) { // No format characters.
2048 // Create a string literal with no \n on it. We expect the constant merge
2049 // pass to be run after this pass, to merge duplicate strings.
2050 FormatStr = FormatStr.drop_back();
2051 Type *Ty = CI->getArgOperand(0)->getType();
2052 Value *GV = B.CreateGlobalString(FormatStr, "str",
2053 Ty->getPointerAddressSpace());
2054 GV = B.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(GV, Ty);
2055 return emitPutS(GV, B, TLI);
2056 }
2057
2058 // Optimize specific format strings.
2059 // printf("%c", chr) --> putchar(chr)
2060 if (FormatStr == "%c" && CI->getNumArgOperands() > 1 &&
2061 CI->getArgOperand(1)->getType()->isIntegerTy())
2062 return emitPutChar(CI->getArgOperand(1), B, TLI);
2063
2064 // printf("%s\n", str) --> puts(str)
2065 if (FormatStr == "%s\n" && CI->getNumArgOperands() > 1 &&
2066 CI->getArgOperand(1)->getType()->isPointerTy())
2067 return emitPutS(CI->getArgOperand(1), B, TLI);
2068 return nullptr;
2069}
2070
2071Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizePrintF(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2072
2073 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
2074 FunctionType *FT = Callee->getFunctionType();
2075 if (Value *V = optimizePrintFString(CI, B)) {
2076 return V;
2077 }
2078
2079 // printf(format, ...) -> iprintf(format, ...) if no floating point
2080 // arguments.
2081 if (TLI->has(LibFunc_iprintf) && !callHasFloatingPointArgument(CI)) {
2082 Module *M = B.GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->getParent();
2083 FunctionCallee IPrintFFn =
2084 M->getOrInsertFunction("iprintf", FT, Callee->getAttributes());
2085 CallInst *New = cast<CallInst>(CI->clone());
2086 New->setCalledFunction(IPrintFFn);
2087 B.Insert(New);
2088 return New;
2089 }
2090
2091 // printf(format, ...) -> __small_printf(format, ...) if no 128-bit floating point
2092 // arguments.
2093 if (TLI->has(LibFunc_small_printf) && !callHasFP128Argument(CI)) {
2094 Module *M = B.GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->getParent();
2095 auto SmallPrintFFn =
2096 M->getOrInsertFunction(TLI->getName(LibFunc_small_printf),
2097 FT, Callee->getAttributes());
2098 CallInst *New = cast<CallInst>(CI->clone());
2099 New->setCalledFunction(SmallPrintFFn);
2100 B.Insert(New);
2101 return New;
2102 }
2103
2104 return nullptr;
2105}
2106
2107Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSPrintFString(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2108 // Check for a fixed format string.
2109 StringRef FormatStr;
2110 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), FormatStr))
2111 return nullptr;
2112
2113 // If we just have a format string (nothing else crazy) transform it.
2114 if (CI->getNumArgOperands() == 2) {
2115 // Make sure there's no % in the constant array. We could try to handle
2116 // %% -> % in the future if we cared.
2117 if (FormatStr.find('%') != StringRef::npos)
2118 return nullptr; // we found a format specifier, bail out.
2119
2120 // sprintf(str, fmt) -> llvm.memcpy(align 1 str, align 1 fmt, strlen(fmt)+1)
2121 B.CreateMemCpy(CI->getArgOperand(0), 1, CI->getArgOperand(1), 1,
2122 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()),
2123 FormatStr.size() + 1)); // Copy the null byte.
2124 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), FormatStr.size());
2125 }
2126
2127 // The remaining optimizations require the format string to be "%s" or "%c"
2128 // and have an extra operand.
2129 if (FormatStr.size() != 2 || FormatStr[0] != '%' ||
2130 CI->getNumArgOperands() < 3)
2131 return nullptr;
2132
2133 // Decode the second character of the format string.
2134 if (FormatStr[1] == 'c') {
2135 // sprintf(dst, "%c", chr) --> *(i8*)dst = chr; *((i8*)dst+1) = 0
2136 if (!CI->getArgOperand(2)->getType()->isIntegerTy())
2137 return nullptr;
2138 Value *V = B.CreateTrunc(CI->getArgOperand(2), B.getInt8Ty(), "char");
2139 Value *Ptr = castToCStr(CI->getArgOperand(0), B);
2140 B.CreateStore(V, Ptr);
2141 Ptr = B.CreateGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Ptr, B.getInt32(1), "nul");
2142 B.CreateStore(B.getInt8(0), Ptr);
2143
2144 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 1);
2145 }
2146
2147 if (FormatStr[1] == 's') {
2148 // sprintf(dest, "%s", str) -> llvm.memcpy(align 1 dest, align 1 str,
2149 // strlen(str)+1)
2150 if (!CI->getArgOperand(2)->getType()->isPointerTy())
2151 return nullptr;
2152
2153 Value *Len = emitStrLen(CI->getArgOperand(2), B, DL, TLI);
2154 if (!Len)
2155 return nullptr;
2156 Value *IncLen =
2157 B.CreateAdd(Len, ConstantInt::get(Len->getType(), 1), "leninc");
2158 B.CreateMemCpy(CI->getArgOperand(0), 1, CI->getArgOperand(2), 1, IncLen);
2159
2160 // The sprintf result is the unincremented number of bytes in the string.
2161 return B.CreateIntCast(Len, CI->getType(), false);
2162 }
2163 return nullptr;
2164}
