2166Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSPrintF(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2167 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
2168 FunctionType *FT = Callee->getFunctionType();
2169 if (Value *V = optimizeSPrintFString(CI, B)) {
2170 return V;
2171 }
2172
2173 // sprintf(str, format, ...) -> siprintf(str, format, ...) if no floating
2174 // point arguments.
2175 if (TLI->has(LibFunc_siprintf) && !callHasFloatingPointArgument(CI)) {
2176 Module *M = B.GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->getParent();
2177 FunctionCallee SIPrintFFn =
2178 M->getOrInsertFunction("siprintf", FT, Callee->getAttributes());
2179 CallInst *New = cast<CallInst>(CI->clone());
2180 New->setCalledFunction(SIPrintFFn);
2181 B.Insert(New);
2182 return New;
2183 }
2184
2185 // sprintf(str, format, ...) -> __small_sprintf(str, format, ...) if no 128-bit
2186 // floating point arguments.
2187 if (TLI->has(LibFunc_small_sprintf) && !callHasFP128Argument(CI)) {
2188 Module *M = B.GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->getParent();
2189 auto SmallSPrintFFn =
2190 M->getOrInsertFunction(TLI->getName(LibFunc_small_sprintf),
2191 FT, Callee->getAttributes());
2192 CallInst *New = cast<CallInst>(CI->clone());
2193 New->setCalledFunction(SmallSPrintFFn);
2194 B.Insert(New);
2195 return New;
2196 }
2197
2198 return nullptr;
2199}
2200
2201Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSnPrintFString(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2202 // Check for a fixed format string.
2203 StringRef FormatStr;
2204 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(2), FormatStr))
2205 return nullptr;
2206
2207 // Check for size
2208 ConstantInt *Size = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(1));
2209 if (!Size)
2210 return nullptr;
2211
2212 uint64_t N = Size->getZExtValue();
2213
2214 // If we just have a format string (nothing else crazy) transform it.
2215 if (CI->getNumArgOperands() == 3) {
2216 // Make sure there's no % in the constant array. We could try to handle
2217 // %% -> % in the future if we cared.
2218 if (FormatStr.find('%') != StringRef::npos)
2219 return nullptr; // we found a format specifier, bail out.
2220
2221 if (N == 0)
2222 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), FormatStr.size());
2223 else if (N < FormatStr.size() + 1)
2224 return nullptr;
2225
2226 // snprintf(dst, size, fmt) -> llvm.memcpy(align 1 dst, align 1 fmt,
2227 // strlen(fmt)+1)
2228 B.CreateMemCpy(
2229 CI->getArgOperand(0), 1, CI->getArgOperand(2), 1,
2230 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()),
2231 FormatStr.size() + 1)); // Copy the null byte.
2232 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), FormatStr.size());
2233 }
2234
2235 // The remaining optimizations require the format string to be "%s" or "%c"
2236 // and have an extra operand.
2237 if (FormatStr.size() == 2 && FormatStr[0] == '%' &&
2238 CI->getNumArgOperands() == 4) {
2239
2240 // Decode the second character of the format string.
2241 if (FormatStr[1] == 'c') {
2242 if (N == 0)
2243 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 1);
2244 else if (N == 1)
2245 return nullptr;
2246
2247 // snprintf(dst, size, "%c", chr) --> *(i8*)dst = chr; *((i8*)dst+1) = 0
2248 if (!CI->getArgOperand(3)->getType()->isIntegerTy())
2249 return nullptr;
2250 Value *V = B.CreateTrunc(CI->getArgOperand(3), B.getInt8Ty(), "char");
2251 Value *Ptr = castToCStr(CI->getArgOperand(0), B);
2252 B.CreateStore(V, Ptr);
2253 Ptr = B.CreateGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Ptr, B.getInt32(1), "nul");
2254 B.CreateStore(B.getInt8(0), Ptr);
2255
2256 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 1);
2257 }
2258
2259 if (FormatStr[1] == 's') {
2260 // snprintf(dest, size, "%s", str) to llvm.memcpy(dest, str, len+1, 1)
2261 StringRef Str;
2262 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(3), Str))
2263 return nullptr;
2264
2265 if (N == 0)
2266 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Str.size());
2267 else if (N < Str.size() + 1)
2268 return nullptr;
2269
2270 B.CreateMemCpy(CI->getArgOperand(0), 1, CI->getArgOperand(3), 1,
2271 ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Str.size() + 1));
2272
2273 // The snprintf result is the unincremented number of bytes in the string.
2274 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), Str.size());
2275 }
2276 }
2277 return nullptr;
2278}
2279
2280Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeSnPrintF(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2281 if (Value *V = optimizeSnPrintFString(CI, B)) {
2282 return V;
2283 }
2284
2285 return nullptr;
2286}
2287
2288Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFPrintFString(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2289 optimizeErrorReporting(CI, B, 0);
2290
2291 // All the optimizations depend on the format string.
2292 StringRef FormatStr;
2293 if (!getConstantStringInfo(CI->getArgOperand(1), FormatStr))
2294 return nullptr;
2295
2296 // Do not do any of the following transformations if the fprintf return
2297 // value is used, in general the fprintf return value is not compatible
2298 // with fwrite(), fputc() or fputs().
2299 if (!CI->use_empty())
2300 return nullptr;
2301
2302 // fprintf(F, "foo") --> fwrite("foo", 3, 1, F)
2303 if (CI->getNumArgOperands() == 2) {
2304 // Could handle %% -> % if we cared.
2305 if (FormatStr.find('%') != StringRef::npos)
2306 return nullptr; // We found a format specifier.
2307
2308 return emitFWrite(
2309 CI->getArgOperand(1),
2310 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), FormatStr.size()),
2311 CI->getArgOperand(0), B, DL, TLI);
2312 }
2313
2314 // The remaining optimizations require the format string to be "%s" or "%c"
2315 // and have an extra operand.
2316 if (FormatStr.size() != 2 || FormatStr[0] != '%' ||
2317 CI->getNumArgOperands() < 3)
2318 return nullptr;
2319
2320 // Decode the second character of the format string.
2321 if (FormatStr[1] == 'c') {
2322 // fprintf(F, "%c", chr) --> fputc(chr, F)
2323 if (!CI->getArgOperand(2)->getType()->isIntegerTy())
2324 return nullptr;
2325 return emitFPutC(CI->getArgOperand(2), CI->getArgOperand(0), B, TLI);
2326 }
2327
2328 if (FormatStr[1] == 's') {
2329 // fprintf(F, "%s", str) --> fputs(str, F)
2330 if (!CI->getArgOperand(2)->getType()->isPointerTy())
2331 return nullptr;
2332 return emitFPutS(CI->getArgOperand(2), CI->getArgOperand(0), B, TLI);
2333 }
2334 return nullptr;
2335}
2336
2337Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFPrintF(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2338 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
2339 FunctionType *FT = Callee->getFunctionType();
2340 if (Value *V = optimizeFPrintFString(CI, B)) {
2341 return V;
2342 }
2343
2344 // fprintf(stream, format, ...) -> fiprintf(stream, format, ...) if no
2345 // floating point arguments.
2346 if (TLI->has(LibFunc_fiprintf) && !callHasFloatingPointArgument(CI)) {
2347 Module *M = B.GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->getParent();
2348 FunctionCallee FIPrintFFn =
2349 M->getOrInsertFunction("fiprintf", FT, Callee->getAttributes());
2350 CallInst *New = cast<CallInst>(CI->clone());
2351 New->setCalledFunction(FIPrintFFn);
2352 B.Insert(New);
2353 return New;
2354 }
2355
2356 // fprintf(stream, format, ...) -> __small_fprintf(stream, format, ...) if no
2357 // 128-bit floating point arguments.
2358 if (TLI->has(LibFunc_small_fprintf) && !callHasFP128Argument(CI)) {
2359 Module *M = B.GetInsertBlock()->getParent()->getParent();
2360 auto SmallFPrintFFn =
2361 M->getOrInsertFunction(TLI->getName(LibFunc_small_fprintf),
2362 FT, Callee->getAttributes());
2363 CallInst *New = cast<CallInst>(CI->clone());
2364 New->setCalledFunction(SmallFPrintFFn);
2365 B.Insert(New);
2366 return New;
2367 }
2368
2369 return nullptr;
2370}
2371
2372Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFWrite(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2373 optimizeErrorReporting(CI, B, 3);
2374
2375 // Get the element size and count.
2376 ConstantInt *SizeC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(1));
2377 ConstantInt *CountC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(2));
2378 if (SizeC && CountC) {
2379 uint64_t Bytes = SizeC->getZExtValue() * CountC->getZExtValue();
2380
2381 // If this is writing zero records, remove the call (it's a noop).
2382 if (Bytes == 0)
2383 return ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 0);
2384
2385 // If this is writing one byte, turn it into fputc.
2386 // This optimisation is only valid, if the return value is unused.
2387 if (Bytes == 1 && CI->use_empty()) { // fwrite(S,1,1,F) -> fputc(S[0],F)
2388 Value *Char = B.CreateLoad(B.getInt8Ty(),
2389 castToCStr(CI->getArgOperand(0), B), "char");
2390 Value *NewCI = emitFPutC(Char, CI->getArgOperand(3), B, TLI);
2391 return NewCI ? ConstantInt::get(CI->getType(), 1) : nullptr;
2392 }
2393 }
2394
2395 if (isLocallyOpenedFile(CI->getArgOperand(3), CI, B, TLI))
2396 return emitFWriteUnlocked(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1),
2397 CI->getArgOperand(2), CI->getArgOperand(3), B, DL,
2398 TLI);
2399
2400 return nullptr;
2401}
2402
2403Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFPuts(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2404 optimizeErrorReporting(CI, B, 1);
2405
2406 // Don't rewrite fputs to fwrite when optimising for size because fwrite
2407 // requires more arguments and thus extra MOVs are required.
2408 bool OptForSize = CI->getFunction()->hasOptSize() ||
2409 llvm::shouldOptimizeForSize(CI->getParent(), PSI, BFI);
2410 if (OptForSize)
2411 return nullptr;
2412
2413 // Check if has any use
2414 if (!CI->use_empty()) {
2415 if (isLocallyOpenedFile(CI->getArgOperand(1), CI, B, TLI))
2416 return emitFPutSUnlocked(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1), B,
2417 TLI);
2418 else
2419 // We can't optimize if return value is used.
2420 return nullptr;
2421 }
2422
2423 // fputs(s,F) --> fwrite(s,strlen(s),1,F)
2424 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(CI->getArgOperand(0));
2425 if (!Len)
2426 return nullptr;
2427
2428 // Known to have no uses (see above).
2429 return emitFWrite(
2430 CI->getArgOperand(0),
2431 ConstantInt::get(DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext()), Len - 1),
2432 CI->getArgOperand(1), B, DL, TLI);
2433}
2434
2435Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeFPutc(CallInst *CI, IRBuilder<> &B) {
2436 optimizeErrorReporting(CI, B, 1);
2437
2438 if (isLocallyOpenedFile(CI->getArgOperand(1), CI, B, TLI))
2439 return emitFPutCUnlocked(CI->getArgOperand(0), CI->getArgOperand(1), B,
2440 TLI);
2441
2442 return nullptr;
2443}

2448
2449 return nullptr;
2450}

2652
2653Value *LibCallSimplifier::optimizeCall(CallInst *CI) {
2654 // TODO: Split out the code below that operates on FP calls so that
2655 // we can all non-FP calls with the StrictFP attribute to be
2656 // optimized.
2657 if (CI->isNoBuiltin())
2658 return nullptr;
2659
2660 LibFunc Func;
2661 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
2662
2663 SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 2> OpBundles;
2664 CI->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
2665 IRBuilder<> Builder(CI, /*FPMathTag=*/nullptr, OpBundles);
2666 bool isCallingConvC = isCallingConvCCompatible(CI);
2667
2668 // Command-line parameter overrides instruction attribute.
2669 // This can't be moved to optimizeFloatingPointLibCall() because it may be
2670 // used by the intrinsic optimizations.
2671 if (EnableUnsafeFPShrink.getNumOccurrences() > 0)
2672 UnsafeFPShrink = EnableUnsafeFPShrink;
2673 else if (isa<FPMathOperator>(CI) && CI->isFast())
2674 UnsafeFPShrink = true;
2675
2676 // First, check for intrinsics.
2677 if (IntrinsicInst *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(CI)) {
2678 if (!isCallingConvC)
2679 return nullptr;
2680 // The FP intrinsics have corresponding constrained versions so we don't
2681 // need to check for the StrictFP attribute here.
2682 switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) {
2683 case Intrinsic::pow:
2684 return optimizePow(CI, Builder);
2685 case Intrinsic::exp2:
2686 return optimizeExp2(CI, Builder);
2687 case Intrinsic::log:
2688 return optimizeLog(CI, Builder);
2689 case Intrinsic::sqrt:
2690 return optimizeSqrt(CI, Builder);
2691 // TODO: Use foldMallocMemset() with memset intrinsic.
2692 default:
2693 return nullptr;
2694 }
2695 }
2696
2697 // Also try to simplify calls to fortified library functions.
2698 if (Value *SimplifiedFortifiedCI = FortifiedSimplifier.optimizeCall(CI)) {
2699 // Try to further simplify the result.
2700 CallInst *SimplifiedCI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(SimplifiedFortifiedCI);
2701 if (SimplifiedCI && SimplifiedCI->getCalledFunction()) {
2702 // Use an IR Builder from SimplifiedCI if available instead of CI
2703 // to guarantee we reach all uses we might replace later on.
2704 IRBuilder<> TmpBuilder(SimplifiedCI);
2705 if (Value *V = optimizeStringMemoryLibCall(SimplifiedCI, TmpBuilder)) {
2706 // If we were able to further simplify, remove the now redundant call.
2707 SimplifiedCI->replaceAllUsesWith(V);
2708 eraseFromParent(SimplifiedCI);
2709 return V;
2710 }
2711 }
2712 return SimplifiedFortifiedCI;
2713 }
2714
2715 // Then check for known library functions.
2716 if (TLI->getLibFunc(*Callee, Func) && TLI->has(Func)) {
2717 // We never change the calling convention.
2718 if (!ignoreCallingConv(Func) && !isCallingConvC)
2719 return nullptr;
2720 if (Value *V = optimizeStringMemoryLibCall(CI, Builder))
2721 return V;
2722 if (Value *V = optimizeFloatingPointLibCall(CI, Func, Builder))
2723 return V;
2724 switch (Func) {
2725 case LibFunc_ffs:
2726 case LibFunc_ffsl:
2727 case LibFunc_ffsll:
2728 return optimizeFFS(CI, Builder);
2729 case LibFunc_fls:
2730 case LibFunc_flsl:
2731 case LibFunc_flsll:
2732 return optimizeFls(CI, Builder);
2733 case LibFunc_abs:
2734 case LibFunc_labs:
2735 case LibFunc_llabs:
2736 return optimizeAbs(CI, Builder);
2737 case LibFunc_isdigit:
2738 return optimizeIsDigit(CI, Builder);
2739 case LibFunc_isascii:
2740 return optimizeIsAscii(CI, Builder);
2741 case LibFunc_toascii:
2742 return optimizeToAscii(CI, Builder);
2743 case LibFunc_atoi:
2744 case LibFunc_atol:
2745 case LibFunc_atoll:
2746 return optimizeAtoi(CI, Builder);
2747 case LibFunc_strtol:
2748 case LibFunc_strtoll:
2749 return optimizeStrtol(CI, Builder);
2750 case LibFunc_printf:
2751 return optimizePrintF(CI, Builder);
2752 case LibFunc_sprintf:
2753 return optimizeSPrintF(CI, Builder);
2754 case LibFunc_snprintf:
2755 return optimizeSnPrintF(CI, Builder);
2756 case LibFunc_fprintf:
2757 return optimizeFPrintF(CI, Builder);
2758 case LibFunc_fwrite:
2759 return optimizeFWrite(CI, Builder);
2760 case LibFunc_fread:
2761 return optimizeFRead(CI, Builder);
2762 case LibFunc_fputs:
2763 return optimizeFPuts(CI, Builder);
2764 case LibFunc_fgets:
2765 return optimizeFGets(CI, Builder);
2766 case LibFunc_fputc:
2767 return optimizeFPutc(CI, Builder);
2768 case LibFunc_fgetc:
2769 return optimizeFGetc(CI, Builder);
2770 case LibFunc_puts:
2771 return optimizePuts(CI, Builder);
2772 case LibFunc_perror:
2773 return optimizeErrorReporting(CI, Builder);
2774 case LibFunc_vfprintf:
2775 case LibFunc_fiprintf:
2776 return optimizeErrorReporting(CI, Builder, 0);
2777 default:
2778 return nullptr;
2779 }
2780 }
2781 return nullptr;
2782}

2837bool
2838FortifiedLibCallSimplifier::isFortifiedCallFoldable(CallInst *CI,
2839 unsigned ObjSizeOp,
2840 Optional<unsigned> SizeOp,
2841 Optional<unsigned> StrOp,
2842 Optional<unsigned> FlagOp) {
2843 // If this function takes a flag argument, the implementation may use it to
2844 // perform extra checks. Don't fold into the non-checking variant.
2845 if (FlagOp) {
2846 ConstantInt *Flag = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(*FlagOp));
2847 if (!Flag || !Flag->isZero())
2848 return false;
2849 }
2850
2851 if (SizeOp && CI->getArgOperand(ObjSizeOp) == CI->getArgOperand(*SizeOp))
2852 return true;
2853
2854 if (ConstantInt *ObjSizeCI =
2855 dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(ObjSizeOp))) {
2856 if (ObjSizeCI->isMinusOne())
2857 return true;
2858 // If the object size wasn't -1 (unknown), bail out if we were asked to.
2859 if (OnlyLowerUnknownSize)
2860 return false;
2861 if (StrOp) {
2862 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(CI->getArgOperand(*StrOp));
2863 // If the length is 0 we don't know how long it is and so we can't
2864 // remove the check.
2865 if (Len == 0)
2866 return false;
2867 return ObjSizeCI->getZExtValue() >= Len;
2868 }
2869
2870 if (SizeOp) {
2871 if (ConstantInt *SizeCI =
2872 dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CI->getArgOperand(*SizeOp)))
2873 return ObjSizeCI->getZExtValue() >= SizeCI->getZExtValue();
2874 }
2875 }
2876 return false;
2877}

2911Value *FortifiedLibCallSimplifier::optimizeStrpCpyChk(CallInst *CI,
2912 IRBuilder<> &B,
2913 LibFunc Func) {
2914 const DataLayout &DL = CI->getModule()->getDataLayout();
2915 Value *Dst = CI->getArgOperand(0), *Src = CI->getArgOperand(1),
2916 *ObjSize = CI->getArgOperand(2);
2917
2918 // __stpcpy_chk(x,x,...) -> x+strlen(x)
2919 if (Func == LibFunc_stpcpy_chk && !OnlyLowerUnknownSize && Dst == Src) {
2920 Value *StrLen = emitStrLen(Src, B, DL, TLI);
2921 return StrLen ? B.CreateInBoundsGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, StrLen) : nullptr;
2922 }
2923
2924 // If a) we don't have any length information, or b) we know this will
2925 // fit then just lower to a plain st[rp]cpy. Otherwise we'll keep our
2926 // st[rp]cpy_chk call which may fail at runtime if the size is too long.
2927 // TODO: It might be nice to get a maximum length out of the possible
2928 // string lengths for varying.
2929 if (isFortifiedCallFoldable(CI, 2, None, 1)) {
2930 if (Func == LibFunc_strcpy_chk)
2931 return emitStrCpy(Dst, Src, B, TLI);
2932 else
2933 return emitStpCpy(Dst, Src, B, TLI);
2934 }
2935
2936 if (OnlyLowerUnknownSize)
2937 return nullptr;
2938
2939 // Maybe we can stil fold __st[rp]cpy_chk to __memcpy_chk.
2940 uint64_t Len = GetStringLength(Src);
2941 if (Len == 0)
2942 return nullptr;
2943
2944 Type *SizeTTy = DL.getIntPtrType(CI->getContext());
2945 Value *LenV = ConstantInt::get(SizeTTy, Len);
2946 Value *Ret = emitMemCpyChk(Dst, Src, LenV, ObjSize, B, DL, TLI);
2947 // If the function was an __stpcpy_chk, and we were able to fold it into
2948 // a __memcpy_chk, we still need to return the correct end pointer.
2949 if (Ret && Func == LibFunc_stpcpy_chk)
2950 return B.CreateGEP(B.getInt8Ty(), Dst, ConstantInt::get(SizeTTy, Len - 1));
2951 return Ret;
2952}

3052
3053Value *FortifiedLibCallSimplifier::optimizeCall(CallInst *CI) {
3054 // FIXME: We shouldn't be changing "nobuiltin" or TLI unavailable calls here.
3055 // Some clang users checked for _chk libcall availability using:
3056 // __has_builtin(__builtin___memcpy_chk)
3057 // When compiling with -fno-builtin, this is always true.
3058 // When passing -ffreestanding/-mkernel, which both imply -fno-builtin, we
3059 // end up with fortified libcalls, which isn't acceptable in a freestanding
3060 // environment which only provides their non-fortified counterparts.
3061 //
3062 // Until we change clang and/or teach external users to check for availability
3063 // differently, disregard the "nobuiltin" attribute and TLI::has.
3064 //
3065 // PR23093.
3066
3067 LibFunc Func;
3068 Function *Callee = CI->getCalledFunction();
3069
3070 SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 2> OpBundles;
3071 CI->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
3072 IRBuilder<> Builder(CI, /*FPMathTag=*/nullptr, OpBundles);
3073 bool isCallingConvC = isCallingConvCCompatible(CI);
3074
3075 // First, check that this is a known library functions and that the prototype
3076 // is correct.
3077 if (!TLI->getLibFunc(*Callee, Func))
3078 return nullptr;
3079
3080 // We never change the calling convention.
3081 if (!ignoreCallingConv(Func) && !isCallingConvC)
3082 return nullptr;
3083
3084 switch (Func) {
3085 case LibFunc_memcpy_chk:
3086 return optimizeMemCpyChk(CI, Builder);
3087 case LibFunc_memmove_chk:
3088 return optimizeMemMoveChk(CI, Builder);
3089 case LibFunc_memset_chk:
3090 return optimizeMemSetChk(CI, Builder);
3091 case LibFunc_stpcpy_chk:
3092 case LibFunc_strcpy_chk:
3093 return optimizeStrpCpyChk(CI, Builder, Func);
3094 case LibFunc_stpncpy_chk:
3095 case LibFunc_strncpy_chk:
3096 return optimizeStrpNCpyChk(CI, Builder, Func);
3097 case LibFunc_memccpy_chk:
3098 return optimizeMemCCpyChk(CI, Builder);
3099 case LibFunc_snprintf_chk:
3100 return optimizeSNPrintfChk(CI, Builder);
3101 case LibFunc_sprintf_chk:
3102 return optimizeSPrintfChk(CI, Builder);
3103 case LibFunc_strcat_chk:
3104 return optimizeStrCatChk(CI, Builder);
3105 case LibFunc_strlcat_chk:
3106 return optimizeStrLCat(CI, Builder);
3107 case LibFunc_strncat_chk:
3108 return optimizeStrNCatChk(CI, Builder);
3109 case LibFunc_strlcpy_chk:
3110 return optimizeStrLCpyChk(CI, Builder);
3111 case LibFunc_vsnprintf_chk:
3112 return optimizeVSNPrintfChk(CI, Builder);
3113 case LibFunc_vsprintf_chk:
3114 return optimizeVSPrintfChk(CI, Builder);
3115 default:
3116 break;
3117 }
3118 return nullptr;
3119}
